title: edith's gourmet pork chops
directions: Brown chops and arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, water and thyme.
Heat.
Then add parsley, sour cream and 1/2 can of onions.
Blend and spread over the chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove cover, put remaining onions on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: creme brule french toast
directions: In a small, heavy saucepan, melt butter with brown sugar and corn syrup over moderate heat, stirring until smooth. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Cut bread in 1 inch thick slices, arrange slices in one layer in baking dish, squeezing slightly to fit.

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix, cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool.
Prepare pudding pie filling as directed on package.
Let stand for 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spread over cake. Garnish with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until crumbs brown.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Boil until soft.
Drain. Add butter and sour cream.
Beat.
Slowly add milk*.
Continue beating.
Shake on cheese.
Add parsley and pepper.
Whip until creamy.

title: children's snack
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls. Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Store in refrigerator.

title: curried chicken pufflets
directions: Split each cream puff in half.
Combine undiluted soup, curry powder and chopped chicken and heat through over low heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Fill bottoms of puffs with the hot mixture and replace tops.
Serve at once sprinkled with paprika, if desired.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Melt butter and sharp cheese.
Add flour, cyapepper and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: two cup citrus punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in large container.
Add lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yield:
34 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Make a paste of vinegar and cocoa and add to mixture.
Sift salt and soda with flour.
Add mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and red coloring.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour alternately with 3/4 cup sour cream.
Dissolve baking soda in 1/4 cup sour cream; add to batter and blend well.
Add extract and salt.
Stir.
Bake in pan for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes in pan.
Remove and sift powdered sugar over warm cake.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Let stand in refrigerator until cold. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Add yeast to warm water; let rest for 10 minutes.
Mix scalded milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to 85°. Beat 1 egg and add to yeast mixture.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat in half of flour (sifted).
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour and mix the dough until it blisters.
Place in greased bowl; cover, place in refrigerator.
To bake, form into two loaves.
Let rise for 1 hour before baking.

title: cherry cake
directions: Bake at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and place in greased casserole. Combine brown sugar, flour, margarine and pecans and sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended. Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
In a bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with milk to the sugar and butter mixture.
Stir by hand just to moisten ingredients. Stir in cranberries.
Spoon into 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 18 muffins.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except the flavoring and the food coloring in a saucepan.
Let heat until 300°.
Take off of heat.
Add coloring and flavoring.
Have cookie sheet lined with powdered sugar.
Pour in a sheet and allow to cool.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Grate cheese.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add flour, stir to mix.
Add milk, a little at a time, stirring constantly. Continue until you have added all the milk.
Add grated cheese; melt.
Pour over noodles in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cook on 450° until brown.
Let cool about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey coconut squares
directions: Bake oblong cake as directed.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, drizzle 1/2 cup honey over top.
Sprinkle with 1 cup coconut and slip under broiler a few minutes to toast coconut.
Best when served warm.

title: "hide ems" cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; bring to a rapid boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until well mixed.
Pour over corn flakes and mix well. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and cool.
Then hide em.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
after
each.
Add
sifted flour and vanilla.
Fold in 7-Up or ginger ale.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in tube pan.

title: honey oatmeal drop cookies(makes 22 (2-inch) cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 large cookie sheets with Pam. In large mixing bowl, combine oat bran, oatmeal, flour, baking powder and allspice.
In blender or food processor, combine oil, egg whites, vanilla, honey and brown sugar.
Blend these liquids into dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon of batter onto the prepared cookie sheets and bake 12 to 14 minutes.

title: hoppin juan skillet cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, coarsely mash black-eyed peas. Add rice, onion, bread crumbs, mayonnaise dressing, chili powder, cumin and red pepper.
Divide mixture into 8 (1/3 cup) portions. Shape each portion into a 1/2-inch thick patty.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut up and fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.

title: cauliflower with tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim cauliflower into small florets. Brush a deep ovenproof dish with melted butter or oil.
Place florets in dish.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Add the fresh bread crumbs and toss over medium heat until crisp and golden.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels. Combine tomato pasta sauce.
Pour over cauliflower in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with combined bread crumbs and cheeses.
Sprinkle with extra pepper.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cauliflower is tender, cheese has melted and top is brown.
Serves 4. Prep time: 20 minutes.
Total cooking time:
20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach crunch
directions: Place peaches in baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine flour, sugar, & egg until lumpy. Spread over peaches. Pour butter over mixture. Bake at 375 degrees for 30-35 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Put fruit &/or pie filling in bottom of pan.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted oleo over cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato and pear chutney
directions: Mix all ingredients except pimentos.
Boil slowly for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add pimentos; boil for 5 minutes more. Pack into jars and seal.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice and peel in large freezer container.
Slowly stir in cream and salt, blending well.
Cover and freeze until firm outside but still soft in center.
Stir several times.
Freeze until firm.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in oil and drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Several cans of kidney beans may also be added.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
To this hot mixture, add fruit.
Place half of mixture in oblong dish.
Place in refrigerator and let set.
Then spread evenly and thinly 1/2 pint sour cream.
Spread remaining half of jello mixture and let set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix celery soup, chicken soup and milk; heat.
Add rice to soup mix.
Put
into
greased
9 x 13-inch pan and top with pork chops or
chicken
with
1	package dried onion soup mix. Cover with tinfoil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in an iron skillet at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: After cream cheese has softened, put in a blender or mixer and add each additional ingredient.
Keep refrigerated.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with pepper and pimientos.
Stuff mixture into hollow of celery stalk.

title: italian mushroom gravy
directions: Heat oil in frypan over medium heat.
When hot, add parsley, garlic, rosemary, thyme, sage and vegetables.
Cook until vegies are soft.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomatoes and their liquid (break up tomatoes), plus the red pepper.
Chop mushrooms and add to pan along with water.
Can use dried Italian mushrooms with this water as a soaking liquid.
Cover and simmer until thick, about 3 hours. Add salt to taste.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and mold into a loaf in baking dish or pan.
Place celery and carrots along sides and at ends of meat loaf.	Salt vegetables and add water; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter maple syrup
directions: Heat together in 1 qt saucepan over medium heat about 3 minutes, stirring constantly, until smooth, hot and bubbly. Pour over hot pancakes or homemade biscuits.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place meaty spareribs in a pan under your broiler until brown on both sides.
Transfer the ribs to a deeper pan and cover with barbecue sauce.
Cover with a tight lid and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: "watermelon rind" pickle
directions: Day 1:	Peel and seed chunk cucumbers to make 8 quarts. Cut into chunks and soak 24 hours in
2 cups lime mixed with 8 quarts cool water.

title: date nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan(s).
Measure all ingredients into a large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan(s).
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Stir in salt. Spread into 9 inch pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese. Stir milk, eggs and Bisquick mix with fork until blended. Pour on top of ground beef and cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hot fish shop tartar sauce
directions: Chop onion and pickle very small. Mix all ingredients together. Chill.

title: ft. henry dip
directions: Put in blender and mix well.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: quick candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by the spoonful on wax paper.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour and cream of tartar; add.
Mix together, then roll into small balls. Roll them into cinnamon and sugar mixture. Makes about 5 or 6 dozen.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together orange juice concentrate and milk until frothy. Add vanilla pudding.
Beat for 1 minute (should thicken).
Blend in sour cream until smooth.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Good luck!

title: mexican hominy
directions: Melt oleo.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until tender. Empty the 2 cans of hominy, draining one and draining 1/2 of the other can.
Mix in with the onion and bell pepper mixture.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and pimento until melted and mixed well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake until bubbly.

title: apple bits mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Stir over hot water until dissolved. Add all remaining ingredients except apple.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in apples.
Spoon into individual molds or small ring mold and chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups, 4 servings.

title: chef's salad
directions: Shred lettuce and put into a large bowl.
Cut into strips the chicken, ham and cheese; arrange over lettuce.
Top with thinly sliced eggs and scatter over with onions.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
Roll out the pastry and line a 10-inch pie
dish.	Combine
the
corn
syrup
and	sugar in a saucepan and
bring to a boil.
Cool, stirring, just until the sugar is dissolved.
Beat the eggs in mixing bowl and gradually add the syrup and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour the
mixture
into the pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes to one hour or until the pie is set.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cut pickles in small pieces.
Grate onion.
Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended (use electric mixer for best results).
Chill.

title: bonnie butter cake
directions: Mix all together well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, pecans, marshmallows and dates together.
Add milk gradually until mixture is moist enough to stick together and roll in logs. Roll logs in graham cracker crumbs.
Place logs in aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: In margarine, saute bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Add soup and water.
Blend shrimp and wild rice into soup mixture.
Add water chestnuts.
Put in large ovenproof casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream and candy pie
directions: Spoon coffee ice cream into pie crust, spreading evenly. Freeze until firm.
Place candy in plastic bag.
Crush with rolling pin, mallet or hammer.
Spread fudge topping evenly over coffee ice cream.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of crushed candy.
Spoon butter pecan ice cream over, spreading evenly.
Freeze until firm, 2 hours.
Garnish with fresh whipped cream-rosettes around edge of pie.
Put remaining candy in middle.
Delicious!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peaches.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour mix over melted butter.
Add sliced peaches; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with or without vanilla ice cream.

title: jay's chili
directions: In Dutch oven, saute the first 4 ingredients in hot oil or until tender.
Add meat, 1 pound at a time, until meat loses redness.
Drain.
Add water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring frequently. Season to taste.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Mix together in blender.
Makes 5 (8 ounce) drinks.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cube eggplant and boil until tender.
Soak bread in milk.
Drain eggplant, add bread and milk mixture.
Mix well. Stir in beaten eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in well buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, the onion, salts, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place meatballs in an ungreased baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inch).

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add soup and chopped Velveeta.
Stir constantly until the cheese is melted.

title: pimento cheese sandwich filling
directions: Cream the cheese with mayonnaise and add remaining ingredients; blend together.
Use whole wheat bread for a great tasting treat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything except pecans well.
Add pecans; pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach crunch
directions: Melt oleo in 8-inch square pan.
Stir in flour and pecans and beat in bottom of pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash ripe avocado pulp.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve as a salad, heaped on tomato slices, or as a dip for chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, syrup and milk in a saucepan.
Cook slowly until a boil is reached.
Continue cooking until a soft ball forms when a bit is dropped in cold water.
Or use a candy thermometer, cooking to 260°.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet and allow to melt.
Add drained fruit and sliced bananas.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: creamy cheese soup(debbie loves my cheese soup.)
directions: Put milk in a double boiler and cook on medium heat.
Melt oleo (this can be done in microwave) and add flour to oleo.
Mix well, then stir into hot milk.
Add cheese, ham and carrots and cook for 20 minutes.
Do not let double boiler boil dry!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter and banana cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter in large bowl until creamy. Add banana and peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Blend in egg, apple juice concentrate and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped peanuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Top each with one peanut, if desired.
Bake for 8 minutes, or until set.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Grease potatoes and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until done.
Brown hamburger meat and mix with taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
(Be sure meat is drained.)
In a double boiler or microwave, melt Velveeta cheese mixed with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir frequently.
To serve, slice hot potato and lightly fluff.
Layer taco meat, cheese mixture, sour cream, green onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Spread on tortillas.
Fold tortilla and dampen edges.
Cook in oven at 350 about 15 minutes in greased pan.

title: tri-level brownies
directions: For bottom layer, stir together first 4 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in 6 tablespoons melted butter.
Pat in a 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix and put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken, onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through. Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork. Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes. Serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender. Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Cover tightly with foil.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Note:
For a fuller pie use the 4 cups of apples, 6 ounces juice and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Other ingredients remain the same or can be adjusted to suit your taste.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion.
Put 2 tablespoons on slice of ham and spread.
Roll like a jellyroll.
Refrigerate 2 hours until cold and cut in bite size pieces.

title: cake donuts
directions: Cream butter, potatoes and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, nutmeg and vanilla.
Sift baking powder with flour.
Stir in mixture and add more flour to make a soft dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick; cut and deep-fry.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine with all other ingredients in a crock-pot.
Heat on low for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper in a grocery sack.
Place chicken in bag, 3 pieces at a time, and shake until well coated.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and let stand several hours.
Use with a variety of fresh vegetables.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5
ingredients together.
Mix next 3 ingredients together to make
dressing.
Pour dressing over salad and let set for at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: california breakfast
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, shredded Jack cheese and melted butter.
Blend smoothly and stir in chilies.
Pour mix into well-greased 9-inch square dish.
Bake in 350° preheated oven 35 minutes or until top is lightly brown and center appears firm.
Cut in squares and serve hot.
Serve with coarsely chopped and sauteed red pepper and green onions.
Accompany with bran muffins.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Mix together milk, vanilla and egg.
Sift together plain flour, salt and soda.
Mix all ingredients, gradually adding flour mixture.
Shape into balls about the size of a quarter and roll in white sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. Take out and press a chocolate kiss on top and bake about 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Break bread into small pieces in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into nonstick muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes in loaf pan.

title: lemon barbeque pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil; drain.
Place chops in baking dish and top with lemon slices.
Mix catsup, vinegar, water and sugar.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or more. Serves 4 to 6.
Can prepare ahead of time and be baked when ready to serve.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° to 450° for another 10 to 12 minutes, or until potatoes are golden brown and cheeses are melted.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown salt pork in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onions and saute until they begin to turn yellow.
Add the water and bring to a boil.
Add the potatoes, creamed corn and frozen corn; reduce heat and simmer for 35 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, milk and butter; simmer for 5 minutes and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until it's ready to set.

title: strawberry bread loaf
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, mixing with a fork.
Beat eggs, oil and berries until well blended, then add flour/ sugar mixture and mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Spray mold with Pam.
In a saucepan, heat soup, stirring in cheese until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin with water; add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.
Serves 45.

title: pepparkakor (swedish ginger cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses, egg and vinegar. Stir flour with spices and salt, then blend with batter.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll out to 1/8-inch and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Frost or leave plain.
Enjoy!

title: no-crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut; mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: In casserole dish, layer pineapple and cream cheese.
In double boiler, mix flour, sugar, egg and juice.
Cook until thick. Pour over pineapple and cream cheese.
Top with marshmallows. Cook in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until it bubbles good.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in wine, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.

title: last of the garden green tomato chow
directions: Grind first 6 ingredients together.
Add salt.
Let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Drain and rinse well.
Add celery seed, mustard seed, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
(No cooking.) Put in jars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and mix with other ingredients.
Top with oleo and crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Blend together milk, vanilla, instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix both mixtures together.
Crush up Oreos in a blender.
Layer crushed cookies and mixture.
Start with cookies and end with cookies.
You can layer this in a plastic flowerpot and add silk flower in the top.
You can also add gummy worms in the layers or on top, if desired.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (375° for high altitude).
Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Stir in taco seasoning, tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 35 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomato and shredded lettuce.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Arrange washed, dried chicken pieces in a large casserole dish.
Pour Ragu sauce over top, covering pieces well.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is very well done.
Serve over hot, buttered spaghetti or fettucine.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken (or pork chops)
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken parts or pork chops in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered. Use 6 to 8 chicken parts or 6 pork chops.
You can use more or less as desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese and add rest of ingredients.
Shape into ball and refrigerate.
Roll ball into nuts.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix dry pudding, Cool Whip and pineapple and juice until well blended. Stir in apples, marshmallows and peanuts or candy bars until thoroughly combined.
Refrigerate until served. Best if eaten within 24 hours. Tastes like a caramel apple.

title: microwave country breakfast
directions: Microwave sausage and onion, uncovered, in a shallow, 2-quart casserole on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until sausage is no longer pink.
Stir twice during cooking.
Remove sausage and onion from dish with slotted spoon and drain on paper towel.
Add potatoes to the casserole with the sausage drippings and microwave, covered, until potatoes are cooked, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt and spread potatoes evenly in the dish.
Combine eggs, milk, remaining salt and pepper in a 2-cup measure.
Pour evenly over potatoes.
Mix sausage mixture with thyme and sage in a small bowl and sprinkle over potatoes. Microwave, uncovered on High for 3 minutes.
Lift eggs at edge with spatula to distribute uncooked portion of egg mixture evenly. Do not stir potatoes and sausage.
Microwave, uncovered, at 50% power (Medium) until eggs are almost set, about 8 to 10 minutes. Give dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Serves 4.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Saute minced onion and green pepper in butter to soften.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Grate first two cheeses and mix with other ingredients.
Make rolls or balls and roll in chili powder and chopped pecans.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cool and chill.
At serving time, add:

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package.
Fill cupcake pans 2/3 full.
Cream the cheese with sugar, salt and egg; stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop one rounded teaspoon cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.
When cool, frost with any white buttercream frosting.
Makes 30 cupcakes.
These cupcakes freeze well.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grate ham or Spam.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add chopped olives, onions, lemon juice, thyme and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve on black bread or assorted crackers.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix both soups, chunk chicken and Veg-All together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick, milk and butter.
Pour over chicken mixture and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugars and small amount of milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add corn meal and remaining milk. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 325° for 30 minutes longer.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: spanish beef
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain and mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Use jelly roll pan.
Grease and flour pan.
Whip eggs until thick and foamy.
Add sugar gradually to eggs.
Fold in pumpkin and lemon juice. Sift together all dry ingredients and fold into egg mixture, beating just until batter is smooth (can use electric mixer, low speed).
Pour into pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Immediately loosen cake from edges of pan; invert on towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
While hot, roll cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper; brown well in shortening.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Blend any remaining flour mixture with tomatoes; add Heinz 57 sauce, Parmesan cheese, sugar and oregano.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; top with cheeses.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.
Skim excess fat from sauce.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Chill.
Put bananas in blender.
Blend with juices.
Before freezing, divide in half and freeze.
Before serving, thaw 2 hours.
Place in punch bowl and add 3 quarts of Wink before serving.

title: currant wieners
directions: In a large pot or crock-pot, melt mustard and jelly together. Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Bring all this to a boil.
Turn heat to low; cook for at least 1 hour.
If using a crock-pot, just let the mixture cook together for several hours.
A wonderful appetizer.
Kids love them.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Cut loaf of bread in half lengthwise, then into 8 equal crosswise slices.
Combine butter and garlic; mix well.
Spread on all sides of each 8-inch slice.
Arrange on 15 x 12-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all together.
I knead it with hands like bread, as it is stiff.
Form into balls (roll in palm of hands), smaller than walnuts.
Melt together in double boiler 3/4 of 1 block paraffin wax.
Roll balls in chocolate mixture and put on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
I use ice tea spoon with long handle to get them out of double boiler.
If they stick to pan, you can pull them free by pushing them off wax paper by putting your hand under wax paper. Sounds harder than it is.
Makes about 60 to 70.

title: eggplant roll-ups
directions: You will also need baking pans or large foil pans.

title: molded jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until separated.
Add drained crushed pineapple and nuts. Put 1/2 mixture in bowl and set in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes (until slightly gelled).
Remove from refrigerator and spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining jello on top and return to refrigerator.
(Should remaining jello gel, place bowl in warm water and stir until slightly thin.)

title: lo-fat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 18 (2 3/4-inch) muffin tin cups with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.

title: pasta shrimp salad
directions: Toss first 2 ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Add remaining ingredients (except shrimp). Refrigerate.
Just before serving, toss in shrimp meat.

title: bavarian goulash
directions: Heat oil. Add beef and onion, saute until meat is browned. Add tomatoes. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and paprika. Add bay leaf. Pour in stock, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time until 3 have been used.
Then add some flour.
Add 2 more eggs and rest of flour.
Then add buttermilk and blackberries. Bake in loaf pan at 300° to 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: choco-caramel squares
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo, evaporated milk and chopped nuts. Press 1/2 of the mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Pour melted Caramel Sauce over top. Crumble remaining cake mixture over and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: meatless mexican beans
directions: Cover beans with water plus 2 inches more.
Soak beans 10 to 12 hours.
Put in slow cooker.
Add water to cover beans plus 2 inches more and add chili mix, garlic and onion.
After 4 to 5 hours cooking, add liquid smoke and hot sauce.
When beans are done, add salt.
Do not heat beans in microwave as they get hard.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, brown ground beef with onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Drain excess grease.
In a large saucepan (4-quart), combine remaining ingredients.
Refill tomato paste and sauce cans with water and add.
Add ground beef mixture.
Simmer on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 1 pound of pasta.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice off cocktail and add water to make almost 2 cups. Put jello in and add Coke.
Place in refrigerator and let almost jel.
Pour in pecans and fruit cocktail.
Set in refrigerator until jelled.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased sheet cake pan, spread pie filling.
Spread pineapple on top of pie filing.
Spread cake mix on top of pineapple.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Spread nuts and coconut on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix sausage, eggs, crumbs, salt and poultry seasoning.
Melt cranberry sauce and mustard.
Mix with meatballs.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a greased (Pam) 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon dill fish(makes 4 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in oven bag; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add water, lemon juice, garlic and dill to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add fish fillets to bag. Turn bag to coat fish with sauce.
Arrange fish in an even layer; dot with margarine.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top.
Bake until fish is tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.
Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Chill time: 30 minutes.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate until chilled; roll in balls.
Put 4 pecan halves to make legs.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: meringue puffs
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.

Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. After all sugar is added gradually add salt and vanilla. Beat until stiff peaks form and all the sugar is dissolved about 5 to 8 minutes. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on baking sheet. Once cooled, remove and store in airtight container. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in water with oleo until water is evaporated. Cook broccoli
with
onion, celery and green pepper until half done. Do
not overcook; drain, reserving juice.
Mix together broccoli and
rice,
add mushroom soup and 1 can of juice from cooked broccoli.
Put
in
greased
Pyrex casserole, top with Velveeta cheese
and bake in 350° oven until hot and cheese is melted.

title: linda's chicken fingers
directions: Mix egg, milk and poultry seasoning in bowl and set aside. Mix flour, dressing mix, salt, pepper and Accent in large bowl with fitted cover (or gallon Ziploc bag).
Heat 2 cups oil on stove in large frying pan.
Dip chicken strips in egg mixture and then in flour mixture and fry until golden brown, turning once.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Cook tomatoes, rice and Italian seasoning; let it go to boiling.
Turn down heat; cover and let it simmer until rice is tender.
Mix with beef. Pour into baking pan or dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and melt in a 350° oven.
Great.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; peel onion and melt 2 tablespoons butter in glass baking dish.
Slice potatoes and onion.
Alternate layers of each onto melted butter.
Top with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave 10 minutes (or until potatoes are tender.)
This may also be fixed inside foil and placed on grill just prior to cooking hamburgers.

title: taco pizza
directions: Prepare pizza dough.
Spread in round pizza pan.
Place pizza dough in oven to rise about 5 to 10 minutes; dough should not be moist at this time.
Layer the following items in this order: refried beans, hamburger (browned), Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Put pizza in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until hot and cheese has melted.
Sprinkle shredded lettuce completely over pizza along with tomatoes and onions.
Spoon picante sauce over all the pizza (sour cream optional).
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomatoes on serving plate; set aside.
Whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar and basil.
Stir in onions.
Season with salt and pepper.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over tomatoes.

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Mix sauce all together and pour over spareribs.
Roast ribs for 2 or 3 hours at 350°.
Baste them while baking.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Mix well; add to margarine and sugar mixture.
Mix dry ingredients and add all together.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost when cool if desired.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in saucepan.
Bring almost to boil; let cool. Add buttermilk, whipped topping, strawberries and nuts. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Let congeal in refrigerator.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: In small mixing bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 tablespoon honey into warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until mixture becomes bubbly.
In small saucepan, combine remaining honey with milk, butter and salt.
Cook over low heat until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast mixture. Combine wheat germ and whole wheat flour in a large mixing bowl. Add liquid mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in a large lightly greased bowl.
Turn dough over to bring greased side up. Cover with greased waxed paper and a towel.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: raspberry poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender; blend for about 40 seconds or until dressing has a creamy pink appearance.

title: pork chops hungarian
directions: Trim fat off chops.
Brown chops in small amount of shortening in 8-inch pan.
Drain fat.
Combine onion, caraway, salt, paprika, dill weed, garlic powder and water.
Add to pan; cover and cook over medium heat for 1 hour until chops are tender.
Watch the juice!
It evaporates; add water every so often.
Transfer chops to warm platter.
Stir sour cream into juice in pan.
Heat through.
Do not boil!
Spoon over chops.

title: monkey bread
directions: Soften yeast in water. Heat milk and shortening together until melted
(don't
boil).
Measure
sugar
and salt into large bowl. Add
hot
milk
mixture.
Stir until dissolved and cool until lukewarm.
Add
cups
of
flour to milk mixture. Mix for 1 minute
with
electric
mixer
or by hand.	Stir in softened yeast and eggs.
Beat well and add more flour to make thick batter. Beat
thoroughly until smooth and elastic about 2 minutes. Cover and
let
rise
in	warm place until bubbly, about	1 hour.
Stir down.
Place
on
floured
board.
Knead lightly and roll out
to not quite an inch thick and punch out with cookie cutter.
Dip each
piece in 1 stick melted butter and drop in
Bundt
pan. Repeat
process layering in tiers in pan.
Pour remaining
butter on top.
Cover again and let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma e's molded shrimp salad
directions: Mix tomato juice, bay leaf, salt, cayenne pepper, chopped onion and celery (also chopped).
Put in saucepan and simmer 10 minutes.
Soften gelatine in cold water and dissolve in hot tomato juice mixture.
Add vinegar, remove bay leaf and cool.

title: jennifer's colored sugar
directions: You can save money by making your own colored sugar!
Put sugar in Ziploc bag.
Add 3 or 4 drops of food coloring to bag and seal. Knead the bag until the sugar is uniformly colored.
If the sugar is too light, add more food coloring.
If the sugar is too dark, add more sugar.
To make unusual colors, mix the food coloring in a spoon and stir with a toothpick before adding to the sugar.
We use these sugars for decorating cookies, etc.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook onions, celery and pepper in oil until they are clear. In baking dish, add milk and butter and spread on bottom.
Add layer of noodles.
Add layer of celery, onions and pepper.
Add layer of English peas, then add soup.
Add shrimp and crab meat. As you make these layers, at this point, add garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add a little of the sherry.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Add buttered cracker crumbs just before taking the casserole out of the oven.

title: great aunt elsie's cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs. Add sour cream and vanilla.
Stir well.
Gradually add the remaining dry ingredients.
On a well floured surface, roll out the cookie dough.
Cut with cookie cutters in desired shapes. Bake for approximately 12 minutes or just until lightly brown on bottom.
Cool and then frost and decorate.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add vanilla, sour cream and egg. Beat until smooth. Stir in apples and salt. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°. Bake about 30 minutes longer. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with topping crumbs. Return to oven and bake 10 minutes.

title: cranberry fruit tarts
directions: Thicken cranberries with cornstarch.
Combine flour, shortening and milk.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with 4-inch cutter. Spoon 1 teaspoon of cranberries on each one.
Go around each with milk to seal edges.
Cover and seal with a fork to crimp.
Lightly grease sheet to bake.
Bake at 375° 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili cheese
directions: *Can try Mexican varieties, according to taste.

title: french dressing
directions: Heat cream until bubbles begin to form around edge.
Remove from heat and add chocolate.
Stir gently until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Stir in brandy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain. Mix soups, tomatoes, chili powder and 1/2 cup cheese. In a 9 x 13 baking dish, cover bottom with crushed Doritos. Pour ground beef on top of Doritos, then pour soup mixture on top of ground beef. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn, then put in oblong glass casserole dish.
Then combine soup, sour cream, cheese and celery.
Mix all together.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil, then cool.
Mix Jell-O and water to cool pineapple.
Chill in refrigerator.
Fold in large Cool Whip.
Chill and serve on lettuce or with any vegetable.

title: party tea
directions: Simmer tea, cloves and cinnamon sticks in 1 quart of water for about 15 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water, then add enough cold water to make 3/4 gallon.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix all together and serve hot or cold.

title: magic coconut pie
directions: Put the ingredients in a blender; blend about 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased and floured pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Glass pie plate works well.

title: mushroom ring italienne
directions: Chop mushrooms and onion very fine.
Saute onion and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter 5 minutes.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and mix in flour.
Gradually pour in milk.
Stir constantly.
Combine with mushrooms.
Cool.
Add egg yolks.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mushroom mixture with parsley and Cappicola.
Add seasonings.
Pour into greased and floured ring mold.
Place in pan of boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups all-bran, let cool.
Cream margarine, sugar, add eggs.
Sift soda in flour.
Add to cream mixture, buttermilk, also add the all-bran mixture and the remaining 4 cups all-bran.
Stir until well blended; do not beat. Must refrigerate before using, fill well-greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Make only what you need as this batter will keep 4 to 6 weeks.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Beat pudding and pie filling, whipped topping mix, milk and almond extract in 2 1/2-quart bowl on low speed until blended.
Beat on high speed until soft peaks form, about 3 minutes.
Fold in cherries.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Top each serving with 1/2 cup reserved syrup.
Makes 8 servings, 360 calories per serving.

title: au gratin potato casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes until partly done.
Combine
soup,
milk and cheese.
Alternate layers of potatoes and
soup mixture in a buttered
baking dish, adding salt and pepper
as
you
go. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven
and
add onion rings, partially crumbled.
Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash zucchini and cut in thin slices. Peel and cut onions in quarters, then slice very thin. Add to zucchini. Sprinkle salt over vegetables; add cold water, enough to cover. Let stand for 2 hours. Bring all ingredients to boiling point and heat for 5 minutes. Pack hot into hot jars, remove air bubbles. Adjust caps. Process for 15 minutes in a boiling watter bath. Makes about 4 half pints.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix lemonade, orange
juice, pineapple juice and bananas together; divide into 3 parts.
Put into freezer.
When frozen, add 1 bottle of ginger ale
to each part.
Can use all together at 1 time if desired.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add chocolate mixture to this.
Add eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
except
butter
and nuts together. Pour in ovenproof baking
dish.	Saute 1 cup chopped pecans in 1/2 stick butter for 5	minutes.
Put
on top of dip.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Serve with Ritz crackers or one of your choice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Pile lightly in an 8 x 9-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1 cup crushed potato chips (or any kind of crumbs).
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet.
Mix butter or margarine and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flavoring. Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, nutmeg and salt thoroughly. Add to creamy mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add macaroni, salt, pepper, onion and mustard. Pour in greased dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Dot with butter and cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown on top.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Cook sugar and water until it spins a thread.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Pour syrup over egg whites; add vanilla and beat until it will stand in patties.

title: western fettuccini
directions: Cook peas as directed on package.
Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Drain well.
Toss lightly with sour cream, grated cheese and salt.
Add peas to noodle mixture and sprinkle more Parmesan cheese lightly on top.
Serve immediately.

title: omaha potatoes
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine all ingredients except cornflakes. Put them on top.
Bake at 275° for 60 minutes, uncovered in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except sunflower seeds. Toss with dressing and store covered in refrigerator.
Toss in sunflower seeds before serving.

title: good layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter with Crisco and eggs, one at a time. Alternate flour and buttermilk; add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate no-bakes
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: easy bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in a bowl.
Add oil, salt and sugar.
Mix and add 2 cups flour.
Stir well.
Add 3rd cup of flour.
Leave in bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Pour out on floured board.
Knead about 10 strokes.
Put in greased pans; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate walnut sensations
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips (save 2/3 cups chocolate chips for top).
Spread into 9-inch square pan.
Bake 23 to 25 minutes.

title: gingered chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken.
Drain oranges, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Cook ginger in hot oil 30 seconds.
Add chicken and stir-fry about 3 minutes.
Add snow peas, reserved syrup and stir-fry sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 2 minutes.
Top with orange sections.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings, about 300 calories.

title: virginia baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Chop onion and garlic.
Fry in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat until soft.
Add vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix the drained kidney beans and butter beans in a large baking dish with the baked beans.
Crumble bacon and add, then mix in the onion and sugar mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 10 x 12-inch greased baking dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Spread 1/2 over batter and 1/2 of nuts.
Then add rest of batter, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
You can use any flavor cake mix and instant pudding you like.

title: orange punch
directions: In a gallon jug, dissolve acid in 1/4 can orange juice; add remaining juice and sugar.
When dissolved, finish filling jar with water.
Cover and let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: lemon squares
directions: Beat eggs with the salt, sugar and baking powder until very light and fluffy.
Add the lemon juice and rind.
Remove crust from oven.
Pour lemon
mix over it.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, pour sparkling wine or champagne over thawed strawberries.
Allow mixture to stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir in the wine and lemonade and dilute with ginger ale and ice cubes as desired.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup mix with bread crumbs. Dip chicken in bread crumb mixture, coating well.
In lightly greased pan, put chicken, then drizzle with butter.
Bake, turning once, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: championship chicken breasts
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard and honey.
Place chicken on grill or rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of the salad dressing mixture.
Grill or broil 8 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue broiling or grilling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown chuck and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: puffy fried bread
directions: Sift flour, measure, and sift again with salt, baking powder, and sugar. Cut in shortening, and add milk to make a soft dough just firm enough to roll. Cover bowl and let dough stand for 30 to 60 min. Roll 1\4 inch thick on lightly floured surface. Cut into diamond shaped pieces.

Heat about 1 inch of oil in frying pan 370° to 380°. Add a few pieces at a time; turn at once, so they will puff evenly. Then turn back to brown on both sides. Drain on paper toweling. Serve with butter or honey. Makes 4 dozen.

title: belvie's favorite cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients, beating well.
Then add pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cold bean salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and pudding mix; fold in half of the whipped topping.
Layer pudding, cookies and bananas in dish; top with remaining topping. Chill.

title: hershey's syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with syrup.
Bake 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: old fashioned cornbread dressing
directions: Combine cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add 2 eggs, buttermilk and bacon drippings. Mix well.
Place a well-greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet in oven at 450° for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Pour batter into skillet. Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and crumble cornbread into large bowl.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In heavy 4-quart kettle, melt 1 tablespoon oleo over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute, stirring until onion is transparent and set aside.

title: fruit cake
directions: Place fruit and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over them.
Mix well.
Beat eggs, melted butter and flour together with flavoring.
Pour over fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in tube pan. Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and place in mold.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf layered
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine beef, salt, pepper, onion and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Fill pan with three layers of meat and two layers of stuffing, beginning and ending with meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar and Crisco, then add milk, flour, baking powder, vanilla and lemon extract.
Add beaten egg whites.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour; last 15 minutes at 325°.

title: rice artichoke
directions: Cook the Rice-A-Roni as directed in large skillet.
Add the green pepper, onions, celery and artichoke hearts to the skillet with the Rice-A-Roni.
Mix the mayonnaise, lemon juice and dry mustard or curry powder.
Mix this into the skillet and serve.

title: soft and easy cheese ball
directions: Set cheeses out until softened to room temperature and mix together.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Chill for several hours. Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Cheese ball will be very soft.
Keep cool.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted margarine. Add nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and blend 1/3 cup evaporated milk into caramels.
Pour over cake mix. Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel.
Crumble rest of cake mix on top.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: hasty hobo soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onions in butter until slightly soft.
Add drained beans, frozen vegetables, ham and rice.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring to coat with butter.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well.
Combine beef and next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased baking dish.
Arrange bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry with mushrooms
directions: Partially freeze beef; cut on the bias into thin bite-size strips.
For marinade, in a medium mixing bowl, stir together water, soy sauce, wine, cornstarch and molasses.
Add beef, stirring to coat well.
Cover and marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes or in the refrigerator for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain well, reserving marinade.
Set aside.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Skin & extract seeds, mash with a fork. Place all ingredients in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until baked solid and a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in milk. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the batter, stirring well.
Toss the fresh blueberries in a little flour, then add them to the batter.
Pour into greased and floured pan.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook and drain tortellini as per package directions.
Set aside in a large bowl.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; add salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients and mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Heavily grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle brown sugar over the bottom of the pan to cover the butter.
Cover this with drained peaches or pineapple. Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over fruit.
Bake as directed or until done.
Serve warm with sauce.
Turn the piece upside down and put sauce over it.

title: oriental chicken wings and drummies
directions: Separate chicken wings at the joints, cut off wing tips and discard.
Mix all ingredients well and pour over chicken wings and drummies in shallow dish.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Place wings on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and put in slow cooker on low until tender.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes; uncover and bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Adjust oven racks to divide oven in thirds.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray a 5-cup loaf pan, Bundt or tube pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: peanut butter quickie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Press with a fork (sugar coated).
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: fried rice and cabbage
directions: Fry rice, onions and pepper in small amount of shortening until it is brown, then add cabbage; cover it with water and add beef and salt to taste.
Add tomato paste.
Let simmer for about 30 to 35 minutes, then serve.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain away any oil. Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese, add in tomatoes and mix well.
Add meats to cheese mixture.
Mix well. Put all ingredients into a large crock-pot.
Let simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken parisenne
directions: Place, uncooked, skinned thighs in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Mix red wine vinegar, water, brown sugar and soup with wire whisk.
Pour over chicken.
Top with mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
One half hour before serving,
mix in sour cream with a spoon.
Serve with rice.

title: quick fudge cake
directions: Mix as directed on box and pour into a nonstick 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake as directed.

title: king's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugars and eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake for 9 minutes at 375°.
Take out before they look done.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Divide the cauliflower into sprigs.
Soak in salt water for a while and rinse well.
Boil up in slightly salted water.
Make a white sauce with the butter, flour and milk, adding enough cauliflower water to make a soft, smooth dough.
Allow to cool slightly and beat in the egg yolks one by one.
Finally, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites to which the corn flour has been added.
Season to taste and line the bottom of a ovenproof dish with the gratin mixture.
Add the cauliflower and pour over the remainder of the gratin mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour testing with a knitting needle.
Serve with cold or melted butter.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in large pot; cook until it falls off bone. Cool; cut into pieces.
Save 1 cup of broth.
Cook spaghetti until tender.
Cut Velveeta cheese into small cubes.
Mix together the chicken, celery, cream of chicken soup, pimento, chicken broth, spaghetti and Velveeta in large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put into a large, long casserole dish.

title: potato leek soup
directions: In chicken stock, cook 2 cups potatoes, 2 whole carrots, celery, leek or onion and bay leaf.
When cooked, remove bay leaf and carrots.
In blender, puree the potatoes, celery and leeks with chicken stock. Return to pan.

title: cheez whiz au gratin potatoes
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Last 5 minutes, sprinkle paprika on top.

title: best-ever cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 1 minute by hand.
Bake in greased, but not floured, 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Chop 1 large jar maraschino cherries (drained) and put on top of cake.

title: snow punch
directions: Beat together bananas, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add cream, 7-Up and sherbet.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: crab salad
directions: After macaroni has been cooked and drained, add chopped vegetables and salad dressing.
Mix and season for taste.
Chill. (When I don't have fresh crabmeat, I use imitation crabmeat.)

title: taco meat balls
directions: Mix and make into small balls.
Cook in microwave for 3 minutes on High.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Store unused batter in airtight container.
Do not stir when ready to spoon into muffin cups to bake.
Can sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar or nuts before baking.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Do not drain liquid from vegetables.
Mix all and marinate overnight. Lasts weeks. Serves 12 to 16.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 3/4 cup pecans.
Mold into 2 small or 1 large ball. Roll in remaining pecans.
Wrap in Glad Wrap and chill.

title: quick quiche
directions: Brown sausage with onions and mushrooms; drain well.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; add sausage mixture.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: spicy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 6 Tbsp juice. Mix pineapple, cheese, flour, sugar and juice. Stir well. Pour into dish. Sprinkle on topping.

title: taco pie
directions: Use a large glass pie dish or a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Spread rolls to form crust.
(Pam the pan first.)
Brown meat and onion.
Add taco seasoning and water.
I bring to boil.
Spread meat mixture over rolls.
Spread sour cream over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream.
Top with crushed Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: mama's lap sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening together.
Add eggs and cream.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with milk. Form into small balls the size of walnuts; flatten with fork. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry and orange salad mold
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Soak gelatin in pineapple juice and dissolve over hot water.
Add to cherry gelatin mixture.
When gelatin begins to thicken, add other ingredients.
Pour into molds.

title: party chicken
directions: Grease one large 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Line with chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with a strip of bacon. Place on beef in casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.

title: tomatoes with basil
directions: Arrange tomatoes on a platter.
Sprinkle with minced garlic, salt, pepper, oregano, basil and cheese. Drizzle oil over all.

title: fifty dollar cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and melted chocolate.
Sift in flour and baking powder.
Add milk and fold in egg whites. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a 350° oven. When done, cool and cover with Fifty Dollar Cake Icing.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix hash browns and milk. Add to onion. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until potatoes are tender and cheese is melted.

title: weight watchers quick dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.
A 1 ounce serving equals 1 Bread.

title: coconut bars(candy)
directions: Melt oleo; add milk, sugar and coconut.
Mix well.
Chill until easy to handle and then form into small balls.
Chill again until firm.
Melt chocolate chips over warm water.
Stir until smooth, then dip the bottom of each ball into the chocolate using a toothpick.
Harden on waxed paper.

title: tex-mex meatball soup
directions: Chop onion.
Cut zucchini into 1-inch pieces.
Combine beef, chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat. Add meatballs; brown well.
Remove meatballs and reduce heat.
Add onion and zucchini.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cumin, oregano, tomatoes with their juice, stock, hot pepper sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add meatballs; heat through.
Sprinkle with fresh coriander.

title: vegetable bean chili
directions: In a 4-quart kettle or Dutch oven, saute zucchini, green pepper, onion, carrots, celery and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in tomatoes, picante sauce, bouillon and cumin; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add beans and olives; heat through. Garnish with cheese and alfalfa sprouts, if desired. Yield: 9 servings (2 1/4 quarts).

title: basic meringue how-to
directions: Note:
A copper bowl is excellent for beating egg whites.
The chemical reaction which occurs between copper and egg whites helps to stabilize mixture.
Cream of tartar should be omitted when beating egg whites in copper bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Break 4 eggs in a bowl.
Beat for several minutes with rotary eggbeater.
Add brown sugar and syrup; stir well.
Add pecan meats and several little pats of butter.
Pour mixture into 2 pie crust shells.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Bake slowly about 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: quick casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thin in a long baking dish.
Add sliced onions and then sprinkle rice over this.
Crumble beef over top of potatoes.
Pour tomato soup over all in pan.
Bake at 350° about one hour.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add yolk of beaten egg. Add pecans and crushed pineapple. Put layer of mixture, then layer of vanilla wafers, etc. Serve with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then spread pineapple on top.
Sprinkle on cake mix, then pour butter over top and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat tomato soup and water in crock-pot.
Brown meatballs.
Add all to soup mixture; simmer for 1 hour.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour 1/2 gallon apple cider into large pot.
Add cinnamon sticks, cloves and orange juice.
Simmer over low heat for 2 hours.
Add more apple cider, as needed.
Fifteen minutes before serving, garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: western sour cream dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients and chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring frequently.
When thick, add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Add meringue and brown.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Step 1:
Toss apples, sugar and spices together.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, adding eggs one at a time. Beat in sifted flour, and pineapple syrup. Mix well. In a 9x13 pan melt butter, pour in brown sugar. Then pour in cake batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. You could place a cherry in the middle of the pineapple rings before baking.

title: italian cheese pie
directions: Note:
Can top with any topping or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: punkie's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Rinse and drain.
Add ingredients accordingly.
Let boil then turn on simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Use 1/4 cup green onion tops for garnish.

title: donna connor's pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2 loaf pans.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Stir in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and juice, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until partially congealed.

title: yummy apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool before slicing.

title: rhubarb cake pudding
directions: Spread each ingredient into an oblong cake pan in order given. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poulet
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine with water; set aside.
Combine onion, celery, salt and mayonnaise.
Mix well with stuffing mix.

title: crisp coconut oaties
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, egg, vanilla and coconut extract.
Combine all other ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; mix well. Add margarine and milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until desired thickness. Stir in vanilla. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: snickers bar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix. Add baking powder, baking soda and flour. Mix well.
Cut miniature Snickers in halves.
Wrap around each bar half, forming a ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into a ball and roll in the reserved pecans.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to ground chuck.
Simmer until hot.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°: spray 8 inch square, 7x11, or 12 cup muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, and the salt.
In a small bowl, beat the buttermilk over the flour mixture; stir just until blended (do not overmix).
Transfer to the pan.
Bake until golden brown and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 20-25 minutes.
Cool pan on a rack 10 minutes; serve warm. Makes 12 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Blend flour and butter in a large pan.
Add cream, soup, salt and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients.
If necessary press dough together. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake until tops are dry and edges are light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: picnic casserole
directions: Fry hamburger loosely in butter with onion; add remaining ingredients.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(If uncovered a tasty crust forms.)

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, save juice.
Put pineapple in baking dish. Combine flour, juice, sugar and cheese.
Pour over pineapple. Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Season meat generously.
In a 4 to 5 quart heavy pot, heat oil.
Brown meat on all sides and remove.
Meat can be cut from bone or cut into smaller servings if desired.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows and stir until melted.
Pour over crumbled crackers and add other ingredients.
Mix with hands as this is a stiff mixture.
Line bowl or pan with wax paper and pack mixture in solid.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: microwave diabetic apple cake
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch round microwave dish (glass preferable).
Set
aside.
Mix
oil,
Equal and eggs together. In another bowl,
mix	remainder of the ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour
into
dish	and stir or fold in the margarine. Microwave on
High	10
to	12 minutes, turning every 3 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice by directions on package.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn and crab bisque
directions: In a 2 gallon stockpot, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add corn, onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute five to ten minutes or until vegetables are wilted.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add remaining ingredients (except marshmallows) to eggs.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While hot, cover with marshmallows.
I return cake to oven until marshmallows lose their shape.
Let cool.

title: traditional chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat margarine in large shallow roasting pan (about 15 x 10 x 2-inch) in oven until melted. Remove.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.

title: holiday cookies(sugar cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl with hands until smooth. Roll dough, one part at a time, 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool; decorate.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken olivia
directions: Mix all except oleo, corn flakes and almonds in large casserole dish.
In frying pan, frizzle corn flakes and almonds in melted oleo for a few minutes.
Spread over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: nothing cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing by hand.
Batter is stiff.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cold, cut into squares.
Don't get upset when the cake looks like it fell.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add dry ingredients. Add crushed bananas and nuts last. Bake in oiled loaf pan in 350° oven.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until done or light brown.

title: corn pie
directions: Whip eggs thoroughly in bowl.
Add sugar, flour, milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Stir in corn.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Set dish in pan of water about 2 inches deep.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean when tested.
You also may use fresh or frozen corn.

title: granny's chocolate dessert
directions: Layer #1:
Mix flour, nuts and butter and make crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma wood's butter sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thick.
Serve warm over berry and fruit pies or dumplings.
Yields approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add shredded zucchini. Add flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour all into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan combine chicken, 1/2 cup of the milk, all the soup and sour cream.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat, spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, beat remaining 3/4 cup milk, Bisquick, corn meal and butter.
