Pour over hot chicken, sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Very fast and easy.
Plus its good.
Feeds about 4 to 5 people.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook chicken in boiling, salted water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture of soup and broth over chicken.
Combine baking mix and milk in a bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
This easy recipe can be prepared ahead and can be frozen.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.
Cool on rack.
Chill for easier slicing.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple and oranges; mix well. Add pineapple and oranges and freeze.

title: mary's goulash
directions: Cut beef into bite size cubes.

Use a large iron frypan and melt oleo, then add meat, onions, paprika, salt and pepper. Brown until dark brown, stirring often. When meat is brown on all sides of cubes, add water and simmer about 35 minutes, covered with lid. Dissolve cornstarch in milk and add to mixture.
Let simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice, noodles or hot biscuits.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender, not brown.
Add chicken livers.
Season with salt and pepper also paprika.
Brown livers. Cover; cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Serve with Sue Tossed Salad in 1988 book, page 19.

title: chicken broccoli crepes
directions: Beat eggs lightly in medium bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Lightly grease crepe pan or 7 or 8-inch skillet and place over medium-high heat.
Pour about 3 tablespoons of batter into pan.
Tilt pan to spread batter evenly. When crepe is light brown and set, turn to brown other side. Remove and repeat to make 12 crepes.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry and pineapple juice with sugar and chill.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale.
Serves approximately 35.

title: ham potato scallop
directions: Cut ham in bite-size pieces.
Put half the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with ham pieces.
Place remaining potatoes on top.
Combine soup, milk, onion, green pepper and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; remove cover and bake 45 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Make pastry for 2-crust pie; line pie plate with pastry.
Fill with sliced apples. Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with shortening.
Top with pastry.
Seal edges and flute.
Cover edge with aluminum foil, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into whipped topping.
Add pineapple, juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash up and parboil until tender; drain.
Add soup and onions to squash.
Add several pats of margarine and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until mixed.
Pour part of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread crumbled Ritz crackers over mixture, then spread a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat, finishing with cheese on top.
Cover and bake at about 400° until bubbling through.
Take cover off and let cook about 10 minutes more.

title: cherry angel cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a large mixing bowl, combine milk, water and extract.
Mix well. Add pudding mix and beat well.

Chill 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread half the cream mixture over cake slices. Top evenly with 1 can cherry filling. Top with remaining cake slices, cream mixture and cherry filling. Chill 4 hours until set. Cut into squares to serve. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla extract.
With wooden spoon, beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: honey of a chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Rinse and drain.
Brown sausage; add onion, pepper and celery.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Add rice, mushrooms and soups.
Pour in greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Toss blueberries with 1 tablespoon flour and set aside. Combine remaining flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine egg, water, orange juice, margarine and 1 tablespoon orange rind.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring well.
Gently fold in berries.

title: sugar-free orange-pineapple salad
directions: Boil water and add jello.
Mix thoroughly.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix 1/4 cup oleo, salt, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Blend well.
Pour over hash browns and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/4 cup oleo and cornflakes and pour over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: german split pea soup
directions: Dice salt bacon and saute with onion.
Pour all ingredients into a Dutch oven and cook for 6 hours.
Serves 10.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in egg. Stir together flour, baking soda and spices.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove and cool on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch square pan. Delicious with spaghetti or chili.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil meat, cut into chunks.
(Save broth.)
Mix stuffing, onions, margarine and put 1/2 in baking dish.
Add meat chunks. Dilute cream of celery soup with can of chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Add another layer of each except this time use cream of chicken soup and broth.

title: banquet potatoes
directions: Thaw frozen hash browns until they can be broken apart and stirred.
Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, in 300° to 325° oven.
Serves 12.
May be made in advance and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: millionaire piesmakes 2 pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie crusts.
Let stand overnight.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Put sugar and water in 2-quart pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour pudding batter into hot syrup, being careful not to mix with syrup.
Cook, tightly covered, for 1 hour on medium heat.
Do not take cover of kettle off while cooking pudding, or pudding will not cook right.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer the following:
lettuce, peas, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Cover mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese.
Top with bacon.
Cover and refrigerate approximately 8 hours prior to serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cool creamy cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, pimento, chives and dill weed in medium size bowl.
Add the salad dressing and toss.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Bake in a buttered loaf pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and slice.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown sausage with garlic.
Add Ragu sauce and tomato paste. Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Cook 16 ounces ziti according to package instructions.
In a large casserole dish, place a layer of ziti, then layer of sauce, followed by cheese.
Repeat process ending with sauce.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix well. Roll into 2 logs. Roll again in chopped pecans or parsley. Chill. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Add spinach and blend.
Chill 2 hours, covered.

title: cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese and eggs sit out and get room temperature. Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and heavy cream for 15 minutes.
Mix graham crackers, sugar and oleo.
Place graham cracker mixture in 10-inch spring-form pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 500° for 12 minutes. Reduce to 250° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off (do not open oven) and leave in oven 6 hours.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) baking pans in large bowl. Stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer 2 minutes. Stir in boiling. (Batter will be thin.) Pour into prepared pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes; cool 10 minutes. Frost with One Bowl Buttercream Frosting.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cukes very thin.
Slice in onions.
Mix in salt. Add one quart very cold water, let stand 3 hours.
Drain well and add pickling syrup of 5 cups of sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons turmeric, 1/2 scant teaspoon cloves, 2 tablespoons mustard seed, 1 tablespoon celery seed, 4 cups vinegar, 1 cup water.
Scald but do not boil. Seal in jars.

title: hot cinnamon biscuits
directions: In an aluminum 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan melt butter, water, sugar and sprinkle of cinnamon over low heat.
Open tube of biscuits and dip in mixture.
Turn over and put on mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scallops with tomatoes(microwave)
directions: Pat scallops on paper toweling.

Place in a microproof 1-quart casserole with onion, wine, tomato paste, tomatoes and cilantro. Toss together until well mixed. Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap and microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until scallops are opaque, stirring once.
Sprinkle with pepper and Feta cheese. Toss together.
Spoon over rice in deep bowls. Serves 2.

title: cranberry slush]
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water; let cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Add remaining ingredients. Let stand overnight in a warm place. In the morning, when it has foam on top, remove the potatoes and discard. Add 1/4 teaspoon of soda and thicken with flour. Let rise. Add 1/2
gallon (8 cups) flour to make a sponge.
Add risen mixture and let rise again. Make out into 4 loaves. Grease pans well. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes or more.

title: vegetable enchiladas
directions: Simmer in covered saucepan the water, lentils and salt for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain, rinse and set aside.
Stir-fry carrots and chili powder in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Add zucchini; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in lentils, half the undrained tomatoes and half of the cheese.
Spoon vegetable mixture onto tortillas.
Place, seam side down, in prepared baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 7 to 12 minutes.
Heat remaining tomatoes.
Spoon over enchiladas.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 minute.

title: granny's beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until brown.
Remove mushrooms, etc.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter to pan. Brown meat. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; pour over meat. Add tomato paste, mustard and salt. Cover and simmer 45 minutes until tender. Combine flour and water.
Slowly stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat. Add mushrooms, onions and sour cream.
Heat, but don't boil. Serve over rice.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat a large pot.
Cook carrots, onion, celery and garlic in 1 cup stock until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans, macaroni, Tabasco and cheese.
Cook until vegetables are tender. In blender or processor, process 1/2 cup garbanzo beans and 1/2 cup kidney beans until pureed.
Set aside.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Add cooked macaroni and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Mix tomato sauce, paste, oregano, basil, salt, garlic powder or clove garlic.
Mix and spread in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Brown and drain ground chuck and mix with remaining sauce.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.

title: oven-fried pecan corn meal chicken
directions: Pound the chicken breast halves to an even thickness.
Pour 1/2 cup of oil into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat it in the hot oven for 10 minutes.
Combine the remaining oil with the mustard, salt, pepper and paprika in a shallow bowl.
Mix well.
Combine the pecans and corn meal on a sheet of wax paper.
Dip the chicken pieces in the seasoned oil and then in the nut mixture.
Remove the pan from the oven and place the chicken pieces in the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes, then turn with tongs and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: penny's baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half. Mix sour cream, lemon juice, and all seasonings. Coat chicken in the mixture. Refrigerate; allow to marinate for 8 hours or overnight. Roll chicken pieces in bread crumbs.
Arrange in baking dish. Drizzle 1/4 c. melted butter over breasts. Bake 45 min. at 350° F. Drizzle another 1/2 c. melted butter over chicken and bake 15 min. longer.

title: dutch potato filling
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Place mashed potatoes in large bowl.
Add slightly beaten eggs, bouillon cube mixture, onion, salt, pepper and parsley; blend well.
Place in a 1-quart greased casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven with chicken, or until browned on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together, making sure spinach is well drained.
Let blend for at least 24 hours.
You can hollow out round loaf and fill cavity with dip using bread as dippers.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (or as directed on package).
Spread out refrigerator roll into triangle shape.
Spread with mustard.
Top with ham, then cheese.
Roll into crescent shape.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: greek vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with a screw-top lid.
Shake well to mix.
Store in refrigerator, covered, for up to two weeks.

title: mexican meat filling
directions: In large skillet cook ground chuck, onion, garlic and cayenne over medium-high heat, stirring often until meat is no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce and cook, stirring often, until thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: easy no crust pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender or electric mixer and pour in a 10-inch, buttered Pyrex pie pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
This will bake to a delicious crust and a toasted coconut top.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large cake pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour over melted margarine.
Heat fruit, such as apples, peaches or strawberries; pour over batter and bake at 350° until brown.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Roll in sliced almonds.
Serve with Escort crackers.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Dip ice cream in
egg,
then
roll
in crushed cookies. Repeat. Freeze at least 24 hours before frying. Deep fry for 1 minute.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Pour sugar over berries; stir.
Let stand while you prepare the Sure-Jell.
Boil Sure-Jell and water for 1 minute at rolling boil.
Pour over berries and stir for 3 or 4 minutes.
Put in jars and freeze.

title: stuffed jumbo shells and tofu
directions: Cook, drain and rinse shells.
Combine remaining ingredients except spaghetti sauce and the extra Parmesan cheese.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Fill shells with tofu mix and place in single layer in baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings. Calories 277.

title: microwave sugar glazed nuts
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream in large microwave bowl.
Microwave on High a total of 7 minutes, 2 minutes and stir, 3 minutes and stir, 2 minutes and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and spread onto waxed paper.
Separate as mixture cools.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell for 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each time.
Add vanilla.
Add soda to buttermilk. Add flour and milk alternately to other ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This cake can be frozen.
It is good plain and/or frosted.

title: dinner salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower, lettuce and tomatoes. Place the vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Grate carrots and add to vegetable mixture.
Stir in cheese and meat.
If adding the hard-boiled eggs, slice them and mix into vegetables. Mix with Miracle Whip and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or toast.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in greased pizza pan.
Bake and cool. Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Layer fruits and top with cherry pie filling.

title: baked seafood rice salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Put in shallow 2 quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and place in a greased casserole dish.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together pecan pieces and coconut.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan. Mix box of German chocolate cake mix according to package directions.
Spread over nut/coconut mixture.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Chill.
Roll in chopped pecans just before serving.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Combine shortening and butter.
Add sugar, then beat in egg. Add salt, almond and vanilla extract.
Last, add flour 1 cup at a time.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 9 minutes or until edges brown.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Finely chop Prosciutto and cook in 4 Tbsp. butter.
Cook until crisp (can do ahead and reheat).

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a 9-inch layer pan. Spread butter evenly. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter. Arrange fruits and nuts in sugar mixture.
Mix 1/3 cup butter with granulated sugar until creamy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly. Add to creamy mixture alternately with pineapple liquid. Spread batter over fruit in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back with touched lightly. Cool a few minutes in the pan.
Loosen cake from sides of pan and invert on serving plate.

title: german potato salad(kartoffelsalat)
directions: *The amount of potatoes used for this tangy hot potato salad will determine the number of servings.

title: peach crumble pie
directions: Line pie shell with plain pastry.
Trim; let rest 10 minutes, then flute edge.
Do not prick.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add butter and work with fingertips until crumbly.
Add 1/2 of this mixture to the peaches.
Mix lightly and turn into pie shell.
Sprinkle the rest of the crumbly mixture over top of peaches.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until peaches are cooked.
Cool 2 or 3 hours on rack before cutting.
Serves 5.

title: teriyaki steak marinade
directions: Mix together.
Pour over meat.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Barbecue or broil meat.

title: creamy parmesan dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth. Cover & Chill. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: libby danti's sauce with sausage
directions: In a large pot, mix tomatoes, seasonings, wine and water. Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
In skillet, fry sausage and remove from pan.
Leave a small amount of oil in pan.
Saute onions and mushrooms. When cool, cut sausage in slices. Add to skillet.
Stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Add to large pot. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and let simmer slowly, covered, 1 hour.
Uncover and continue cooking for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at low heat.
If sauce is too thick, add more water to your taste.
Stir occasionally during cooking.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Beat eggs with vanilla and oil and mix with apples.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Combine with apple/egg mixture.
Blend in nuts; spoon into an 11 x 14 x 2-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Fry sausage, crumbled. Press biscuits into bottom of pan until covered.
Sprinkle frozen hash brown potatoes over biscuits.
Sprinkle sausage over hash browns.
Beat eggs real well with a little milk.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain thoroughly, then mash.
Add all ingredients, except 1/2 of the butter to squash.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour mixture into baking dish, then spread melted butter over top and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: revival goulash
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef; cook until brown. Add soup and cheese.
Use 1/2 can of water to rinse can out.
Add to drained cooked noodles.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Freezes well.

title: chicken and vegetable rice soup
directions: Put chicken broth in large pot with vegetable base.
Simmer on low.
Next, add all vegetables and cooked rice.
Stir occasionally and cook, covered, for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: wendy's 3 layer quick dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; spread in bottom of dish.
Add salsa. Sprinkle cheese on top of salsa.
Heat in microwave for 1 minute. Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!!

title: chili-mac skillet
directions: Drain kidney beans.
In a large skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, uncooked pasta, green chilies, chili powder, garlic salt and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring often.
Top with cheese. Cover.
Heat 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves six.

title: one pan chicken and gravy
directions: Mix all together the soups and pour over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is cooked. Any form or amount of chicken may be used.

title: spiced beef with dumplings
directions: Trim excess fat from roast and melt the fat in a Dutch oven. Brown roast on all sides in the fat.
Add 1/4 cup water and the remaining ingredients except biscuits, parsley and flour.
Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Place biscuits on roast and sprinkle with parsley.
Cover tightly and steam for 15 minutes.
Remove roast and dumplings to platter.
Add flour and 1/4 cup water to pan juices.
Stir until thickened.
Serve with roast.

title: cousin sallie's gingerbread
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, salt and spices.
Combine shortening, sugar and molasses in mixing bowl and beat to blend. Add eggs; beat until thoroughly blended.
Add dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
All vinegar and milk, and stir until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees 45 to 50 minutes.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, mustard, vinegar, sour cream and eggs together.
Cook slightly.
Stir constantly until dressing is creamy.

title: rice casserole
directions: Rinse and drain rice, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 c. tomato juice over rice, then sprinkle with the onion, pepper, and celery (if wanted).
Then the meat, water, and 1 1/2 c. tomato juice.
Cut the bacon in 1/2 and put on top.
Cover and bake at 350°F for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for another 1/2 hour or until bacon is crisp.

title: whole wheat bubble loaf
directions: Generously grease one 2 qt. deep casserole dish or two 8 x 4 in. loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large bowl combine 1 c. bread flour, sugar, salt and yeast - blend well.
In small sauce pan, heat milk and margarine until very warm (120 to 130 degrees).
Add warm liquid and egg to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at med. speed.
By hand, stir in whole wheat flour to form a stiff dough.
On floured surface knead in 1 to 1 1/2 c. bread flour until dough is smooth and elastic about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel. Let rise in a warm place until light and doubled in size, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: london broil
directions: Combine wine, soy sauce, garlic, ginger and parsley in baking dish.
Marinate meat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Broil for 30 to 35 minutes at 550°, turning every 5 minutes.
Baste with mixture at each turn.

title: hot dog hash
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle on flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and hot dogs.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°.
Top with cheese until melted.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Combine flour, oleo and nuts and press in thin layer into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Let cool, then let chill in refrigerator.
Combine softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over chilled crust and return to refrigerator.
Mix instant pudding with milk and vanilla.
Beat until thick and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Top with remainder of Cool Whip.
Will keep 4 to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add ham and Swiss cheese. Split rolls and fill with mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 48 sandwiches.

title: low-fat chocolate fudge
directions: Boil cream, butter and sugar for 5 minutes (start time when bubbling).
Then add marshmallow cream and then add other ingredients.
The strained prunes make this very creamy.
Let set for 2 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dip each tortilla in hot grease just to soften.
On each tortilla put some chicken, onion and cheese.
Roll up and place in 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Mix the soup, milk and chilies and pour over the enchiladas.
Top with additional onions and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil and room temperature buttermilk.
Stir together well (be sure oil is well blended when adding flour).
Add 4 cups flour and mix well.
Then add 5 cups flour (more if needed), salt, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Dough is ready to bake.
Seal mixture in an airtight container and refrigerate!

title: thai ribbons
directions: Soak 30 (6-inch) bamboo skewers.
Combine teriyaki sauce, ginger, oil, garlic and red pepper.
Cut steak across grain into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place meat in plastic bag.
Pour marinade over steak and marinate in bag up to 2 hours.
Thread slices on bamboo skewers.
Place on rack in broiler pan 3 to 4-inches from heat.
Broil 2 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. (Can substitute chicken or pork.)

title: fresh vegetable marinate
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli, cut into bite-size pieces. Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine broccoli and cauliflower with mushrooms, pepper and celery.
Toss lightly. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well and pour over vegetables. Chill and serve.

title: pickled cukes
directions: Soak cukes in lime water overnight (cover).
Drain and wash 3 times in cold water.
Soak 2 hours in salt water.
Drain and wash 3 times in cold water.
Dissolve alum in warm water.
Add enough cold water to cover cukes.
Add cukes and bring to a boil.
Drain and wash 3 times in cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices. Add cukes and bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Yield: 12 pints.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Mix all ingredients, but peanut butter cups.
Roll into balls. Place in greased T-cup tins.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Take
out of oven; insert peanut butter cups immediately.
Let cool.	Remove from tins.

title: chocolate caramel pecan fudge
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts, caramel topping and vanilla.
Spread evenly in a foil-lined 8 or 9 inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix and form into ball and chill.

title: potato onion casserole
directions: In a 9X13 baking dish, layer onions, potatoes, Velveeta. Repeat onions and potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Pour soup over all and top with grated cheese.
(soup may be diluted with 1/3 cup milk.) Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test potatoes for doneness.

title: pull apart cake (breakfast or brunch)
directions: Make night before.
Cover with plastic wrap to allow dough to thaw and rise.
Leave on counter overnight and bake in the morning.
Grease Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle some of the pecans and all the granulated sugar in pan.
Place frozen dough balls evenly on top of pecans and sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon and pudding evenly on top.
Melt brown sugar and butter together and spoon over dough.
(Do not pour over dough.)
Add remaining pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to set for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Flip rolls onto a serving dish.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, Worcestershire and ketchup.
Stir.
Add hamburger and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian pot roast
directions: In a 4 1/2-quart Dutch oven, brown roast.
Drain off fat.
Add water, bouillon, oregano, basil, bay leaves, garlic and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown beef.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour into casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixer
bowl cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and
flour;
add
to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or
until
golden.
Cool
about
hour.
Serve warm. Garnish with whipped cream.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer and fold in 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cut up and add the cream cheese to the meat; stir until melted.
Add the mushroom soup and 1 can of water to the mixture.
(Use less water, if desired.)
Heat through until well blended and hot.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil to 265° (hard ball stage).
Beat egg whites stiff and gradually beat into boiling syrup.
Whip until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper. Makes about 150 pieces.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan with butter (very heavily). Sprinkle pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix as usual.
Add sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla to cake mix.
Mix and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.

title: oven apple pancakes
directions: With whisk or beater, beat eggs, milk, salt and flour until smooth.
Let the batter rest.
Combine the sugar and cinnamon, and sprinkle over the apples; toss to mix.
Generously butter two 9 inch pie pans, using about 2 Tbsp. for each pan.
Divide apples evenly between the pans.
Stir the batter and pour it over the apples, using 1 c. per pan.
Bake at 375° 30-40 minutes, or until pancakes are fluffed, golden brown, and set.
Serve hot in wedges topped with whipped cream.

title: mexican corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chilies.
Mix well. Pour 1/2 corn mixture into a greased long casserole dish. Sprinkle chilies over mixture.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat corn mixture and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.
It thickens some as it cools.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Add sugar to butter and heat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add coconut, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad(for large gathering)
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and let cool. Cut cheese, tomatoes, cucumbers and bell peppers in little cubes.
Mix this with cooled macaroni, relish and Miracle Whip to taste.
(Original recipe did not list quantities or ingredients.)

title: winter vegetable chowder
directions: In small bowl, cover tomatoes with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring broth and 1/2 cup water to boil.
Add potatoes; return to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat for 12 minutes, or just until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove 1 cup potatoes; set aside.
Transfer contents of saucepan to blender; puree until smooth.
Pour mixture back into saucepan.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Place apples in a 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with the mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Melt the butter in a pot.
Add the flour, sugar, egg and walnuts.
Spoon over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream.
Stir in sour cream just before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, cream the powdered sugar, butter, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and salt; blend well.
Fill cookie press; press dough into desired shapes onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes, or until lightly browned on edges.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: margaret's eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, Cool Whip and milk.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers, then with pudding mixture; alternate twice, ending with crackers.
Pour chocolate sauce over all.
Refrigerate.

title: mom's pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mixture evenly into pie crusts.
Then chill.
Whip the cream until stiff.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Spread over top of base mixture and chill thoroughly.

title: cauliflower patties
directions: Cook cauliflower; drain and mash.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Let stand about 1 hour before cooking.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil and cook until golden brown on both sides.
Can be frozen and then reheated as you need them.

title: sausage squares
directions: Combine the biscuit mix and 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage in skillet. Add onion and cook until tender; drain well.
Spread sausage mixture over first layer.
Combine egg, grated cheese and 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Spread over top of sausage mixture. Press lightly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cook about 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: alessa's cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread in a large bowl.
Top with half of beans.
In a medium bowl, combine tomatoes, pepper and onions; layer half of this mixture over beans.
Layer half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing.
Repeat layers, using remaining ingredients.
Garnish as desired.

title: german apple pudding cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together.
Let stand until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into apple mixture.
Add nuts, raisins, and vanilla.
Pour into 8 X 8 inch pan which is slightly oiled.
Bake at 375° for 40 - 45 minutes.
If preferred use unsweetened can sliced apples instead of fresh apples.

title: good n easy crawfish jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in rice cooker.
After cooker chimes, let jambalaya set on warm for 30 minutes before serving. May use shrimp instead of crawfish.

title: banana cream supreme
directions: Crush crackers and combine with butter and sugar.
Press in bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine whipped topping, pudding and sour cream.
Pour half of filling over crust. Slice bananas and layer on top.
Pour remaining filling over bananas, then sprinkle chopped pecans over top.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and finish baking.
When it doesn't wiggle in the center, it is done or when a knife inserted in the center comes out clean (about 20 to 25 minutes).

title: copper carrots
directions: Scrape carrots.
Cut into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Simmer carrots, green pepper and onion in small amount of water over low heat until carrots are tender; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate several days before serving.

title: italian "s" cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, lemon rind and shortening.
Mix into bowl with flour to form a soft dough.

title: ella davis' russian tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and 10x sugar.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 17 minutes.
Roll in 10x sugar while warm and again when cool.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in a piece of bacon.
Put each piece of chicken on 2 slices of dried beef in a casserole dish. Use one so the chicken fits snug in the dish.
Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup sour cream together and spread over chicken.
Bake at 250 degrees for 5 hours uncovered.

title: bourbon pecan chicken
directions: Whisk together mustard, sugar, bourbon, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Set aside.

title: cheezy bacon potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and cut in small pieces; add margarine and milk.
Mix until soupy.
Add onions, green onions and parsley; mix.
Add bacon, salt and pepper.
Bake at 425 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes until perfect consistency.
Melt cheese on top for last 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 25.

title: georgetown red rice
directions: Cook bacon, remove from pan and crumble.
Cook onions in bacon fat until tender, then add red tomatoes, rice, broth, catsup, seasonings and crumbled bacon.
Cook on low heat until rice is done.
Stir several times during cooking.

title: tomato soup
directions: Heat milk in one pan.
Heat tomatoes, tomato soup, butter, flour (mix first in some of the tomatoes) and salt in another pan. When hot, add pinch of soda.
When both milk and tomato mixture are hot, mix together.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish or pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over melted margarine.
Add vanilla to sweetened fruit.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wassail(kids love it!)
directions: Cut orange into eighths, and pierce with whole cloves.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook one hour on high, then four hours on low.
Makes 12 servings.
Can be doubled for a six-quart crock-pot.

title: cheese fries
directions: Bake French fries as directed on package.
Fry bacon; pinch into small pieces.
When fries are baked, pour Ranch dressing on them, then add cheese and top with bacon pieces.
Place back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: fresh corn and tomatoes with curry
directions: Shuck the corn.
With knife, cut kernels off cobs.
There should be about 2 1/2 cups.
Core the tomatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Melt butter into skillet.
Add the scallions and curry powder.
Cook, stirring briefly, until wilted.
Add the corn, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook for 4 minutes over medium to high heat.
Do not overcook.
Serve hot.
Sprinkle with coriander.
Yields 4 servings.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Chop pepper, celery and onion.
Cook until done, then add pork and beans, catsup and brown sugar.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in punch bowl.
Float sherbet in punch.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix these thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts and kindly service. Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten the other ingredients and raise the texture to a great height of Christian living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve it with a smile.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Beat in cream cheese.
Add pineapple after draining.
Add nuts, if you want.
Sprinkle marshmallow topping on top.
Chill until firm.
Any flavor of jello and fruit combination could be substituted.

title: frijoles ala charra
directions: *Add more if desired.

title: boiled dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar, lemon juice, water, butter or oleo.
Cook on low heat until thickened, stirring.
Add beaten yolks and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar with shortening.
Add three eggs, one at a time, beating between each addition.
Add soda, salt, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and pumpkin.
Add flour and beat well.
Cook in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy cherry dessert
directions: Mix melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs in a bowl.
Then press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch bowl or pan.
Combine softened cream cheese (8 ounces and 3 ounces) milk and vanilla in a medium bowl. Beat until smooth.
Spread the following in order over crust: cream cheese mixture, whipped topping and cherry pie filling. Chill several hours.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: french chicken
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with rice; add broth plus water if needed.
Layer chicken over rice.
Mix soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beach party punch
directions: Pour all ingredients into punch bowl with ice ring.
Garnish with orange slices and cherries.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients and put into a greased casserole dish. Cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for another 10 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package and drain well. Combine spinach with other ingredients and shape into bite size balls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crab nibbles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and microwave until cheese is melted. Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.

title: great grandma lockerbie's scones
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in skillet on top of stove, slowly, until done.

title: ramen noodle cole slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar and chicken flavor packet in microwavable bowl for 1 minute in microwave. Add vinegar and stir well. Just before serving, mix first 4 ingredients together. Add Ramen noodles by breaking them up in mixture. Do not cook noodles. Pour the dressing mixture over and stir well. Serve immediately.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix in bowl.
Roll out between 2 sheets wax paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: green salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package. When it begins to set, add rest of the ingredients. Mix well. Let set. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise and crackers.

title: cinnamon hard candy
directions: Cook sugar, water, corn syrup and food coloring to very hard crack stage (300°).
Add oil of cinnamon; stir slightly to mix in oil.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet, cool.
Crack into pieces.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter with 1 cup of milk.
Let sugar and remaining milk come to a boil, then add other ingredients and stir until thick.

title: margaret's favorite meat loaf
directions: In a medium bowl, lightly mix ground meat, bread crumbs, onion, 1/2 (4 ounces) tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan. Combine remaining tomato sauce with rest of the ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Baste loaf several times.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Cool slightly.
Pour into cake mix; add eggs and blend well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle on butterscotch chips and nuts generously.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done. This is a time saving recipe.

title: re-baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and grease with corn oil.
Bake for 5 minutes in microwave or 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Test with fork for tenderness.
Wrap in foil and set aside.

title: fried cheese ball
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add egg whites.
Shape into small balls and roll in fine cracker crumbs. Fry in deep oil at 375° until golden.
Serve hot.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Stir Velveeta and salsa in saucepan over low heat until Velveeta is melted.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: shrimp spread - blender
directions: Put onion, garlic, lemon rind, vinegar, ginger, salt and chili powder in blender jar and blend until finely chopped. Toss in shrimp a few at the time. Mix in sour cream until spreading consistency.

title: scallops and parsley sauce
directions: Heat butter and oil in heavy, large skillet over medium-high heat until butter is melted.
Add scallions and 1/2 cup parsley; cook 5 minutes, or until scallions are softened but not burned. Add wine; cook 2 minutes.
Add scallops.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, for 4 to 5 minutes, or until scallops are opaque. Stir in remaining parsley; season to taste with salt and pepper. Pour over spaghetti; toss gently to mix.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in freezer filling the rest of the way with milk to fill line.

title: amish bread starter
directions: Stir every day for 7 days.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat and saute onion, bell pepper and parsley until onion is clear. Stirring, add the tomato sauce, garlic, mint and wine, then add rice, hot sauce, smoked sausage and enough water to cover the rice by about 1 inch.
Cook until most of the water is gone.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour; don't lift the lid until it has been simmering for 45 minutes.
This makes a red jambalaya.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: granola
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add sweet rice syrup, ice water and olive oil and mix.
Spread in deep, oblong baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add pecans, walnuts and almonds.
Mix and continue to bake 1/2 hour longer.
Add raisins and chopped dates.
Mix and cool.
Store in Ziploc bags.

title: oriental rice casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery and onions.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix in mushrooms, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and soy sauce. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; stir in mushroom soup.
Add to beef mixture.
Stir in rice.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious.

title: meatballs(for macaroni sauce)
directions: Mix
ingredients
well	and
roll into small meatballs. Let 1/2
wedge of lard or some Crisco melt in frying pan.
Put in meatballs, let brown on all sides and remove.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook potatoes in broth.
Chop celery and add.
When potatoes are almost done, add cauliflower and cook until tender.
The potatoes must be very well cooked, otherwise soup will be gluey.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put scalded milk in breadcrumbs.
Add 4 egg yolks, sugar, butter and grated rind of lemon.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites into confectioners sugar until stiff. Spread over bread pudding to seal.
Set into a 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a large pot, put potatoes and water. Bring to rolling boil. Add salt, pepper, celery salt and onion flakes.
Simmer for 10 minutes, then add butter or margarine. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: rich pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil gently 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in pie shell. Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: In a saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for one minute more.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Makes 2 cups.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour over remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool, then refrigerate.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack small firm cucumbers in jars.
For each jar, add 1 button of garlic and 1 umbrella of dill or 1 tablespoon of whole dill seed.
Boil water, vinegar and salt (not iodize) for 3 minutes. Pour over pickles while hot.
(To make sure jars are sealed, can put in cold pack for few minutes.)
Let stand for 4 to 6 weeks before use.

title: shrimp cheese turnovers
directions: Cut butter and cream cheese into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Work with hands to form ball.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
On floured surface, roll half into 11-inch circle.
Cut into rounds with 2-inch floured cutter.
Spread each round with about 1/2 teaspoon of cheese spread.
Top with a few shrimp.
Fold in half and seal.

title: special k bars
directions: Put the cereal in a large bowl.
Bring sugar, syrup and oleo to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; stir thoroughly and pour over flakes.
Mix. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Once the fat has been removed from the chicken, place the chicken in ovenware container.
Season.
Add lemon juice and the chicken broth.
Garnish with paprika.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cocktail wieners
directions: Mix sauce and jelly in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until blended.
Add wieners and heat thoroughly.

title: candied apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry of 2-crust 9-inch pie.
Fill bottom shell with apples.
Combine next six ingredients.
Pour over apples.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown and apples are tender.
Remove from oven.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup of coconut and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: "simply delicious" chicken broccoli lasagna(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Will need a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: dilled macaroni and cheese salad(cold)
directions: Cook macaroni, omitting salt.
Drain well; rinse in cold water.
Combine the next 4 ingredients and the cooked macaroni.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender, except oil. After all is well blended, add oil very slowly. Blend until thick.
Delicious.

title: mil's dressing
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Double recipe for 4 or more people.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Measure by tablespoon, teaspoon or cup and mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix with hands, the first 5 ingredients.
Remove 2 cups of crumbs and set aside.
Mix remaining crumbs with boiling water, molasses and baking soda.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak the Grape-nuts in the buttermilk for 10 minutes.
Combine other ingredients; beat well.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before putting in oven.
Bake 40 minutes at 375° in loaf pan.

title: dolly parton's soup
directions: Cook cabbage, celery, onion and carrots until tender in the least
amount
of
water
possible.
Then
add tomatoes or juice and bouillon cubes.
Simmer until well done.

title: easy refrigerator dough
directions: Measure water and yeast into bowl; stir to dissolve.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and eggs.
Mix until dough is soft.
Do not knead.
Cover with damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
Let set at least 2 hours.
About 1 to 1 1/2 hours before baking, shape into rolls.
Cover; let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° until done.
This dough will keep in the fridge for about 5 days.
Just keep the cloth covering it damp.

title: golden glazed ham with cherry sauce
directions: Place ham, fat side up, on a rack in shallow pan.
Heat in a 325° oven for time indicated on label.
One-half hour before end of time, remove ham from oven and score fat in diamonds.

title: cherry swish
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into each pie shell.
Pour 1/2 pie filling on top of each mixture and swish around until white shows through, making swirls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Put water, cocoa and oleo in pan and bring to boil; pour over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes until done.
Frost while hot.

title: maple flavored seven minute frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease (with extra amount of softened butter) and lightly flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
Combine the butter and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Beat mixture with an electric mixer until well blended and creamy for 2 minutes.
Gradually add sugar while continuing to beat on medium speed.
Beat until the mixture is light and fluffy for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after the addition of each egg until it is thoroughly absorbed.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Slowly add this combination to the egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in the coconut flavoring and vanilla flavoring, then the flaked coconut.
Beat well for 1 minute.

title: oven fries
directions: Cut potato into quarters lengthwise and dry with a paper towel.
Coat all over with the oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in a nonstick pan or a Pam sprayed pan and bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In large saucepan, boil chicken broth and onions.
String beaten egg while stirring.
Add salt and pepper.
Add cornstarch mixture to thicken.
Continue to boil until thickened.
Add corn, if desired.
Serve in bowls.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; heat until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add peas, corn, celery, onion, green pepper and pimiento.
Let chill overnight.

title: peanut butter no bakes
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, milk and salt in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Drop on waxed paper.

title: marinade for deer
directions: Mix in bowl; marinate the deer for 20 minutes to overnight.

title: rum balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and chop nuts.
Combine with sugar and cocoa.
Stir in corn syrup and rum.
Wet hands and form mixture into balls (small).
Roll in chocolate sprinkles.
Freeze on flat tray.
When firm put into container.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: Marinate 3 hours.
Add one large head of lettuce.
Sprinkle on more Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate bubble biscuits
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in 1/3 cup butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in chocolate chips. Add milk; stir until dough holds a shape.
On floured board, knead dough lightly.
Roll dough into 16 balls.

title: apple butter
directions: Cut apples into chunks, but do not peel.
In a glass or stainless steel kettle, combine apples and cider.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat until apples are very soft, about 30 minutes. Press through a food mill or fine sieve and return to the cleaned pot.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until very thick, about 2 hours.
Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate or freeze.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in saucepan over low heat. Stir until
sugar
is dissolved, then cook without stirring to 252° (a little
dropped
into
cold water forms a hard ball). Remove from heat
and
pour,
beating
constantly,
in a fine stream
into
2 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Continue beating until mixture
holds its
shape
and
loses
its
gloss.
Add vanilla and broken nuts.
Drop quickly from tip of spoon onto wax paper or
spread in	greased
shallow
pan
and
cut into squares when firm.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, ginger and baking powder and sift together.
Mix salt, egg, orange juice, butter and water together.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add the nuts and cranberries to the mixture.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until the tester inserted in middle of loaf comes out dry.

title: creamy chocolate squares
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add walnuts; mix well.
Pour into buttered 8-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 2 pounds.

title: shrimp provencale
directions: About 45 minutes before serving in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons of oil, cook shrimp, stirring often about 3 minutes until shrimp turn pink; set aside.
In same skillet, add 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add mushrooms; cook until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes more.
Return shrimp to skillet.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice.

title: chowder
directions: Cook hen , beef and bacon in 1/2 gallon of water for 2 hours. Then add onions, carrots, cabbage, green beans and tomatoes.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Then add potatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Then add corn and cook at least 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 gallons.
It sticks very easily, so cook over low heat and stir often.

title: cheese salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and picante sauce in a 1 1/2 quart microwavable bowl on High for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle on onions towards end.
Makes 10 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook turkey, onion and garlic until all pan juices evaporate and turkey is well browned, stirring frequently.
Stir in chili powder and cook 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes with their liquid, water, salt, sugar and crushed red pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Gently stir in kidney beans and heat through.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with margarine.
Put coconut and pecans in margarine covered pan.
Mix cake mix as directions instruct.
Pour cake mix over pecan mixture.
Soften cream cheese and 1 stick of margarine.
Mix the powdered sugar with enough milk to make a thin cake icing.
Now mix cream cheese mixture and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Now bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Cake is done when cracks appear in cake.

title: mushrooms and steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 servings. Melt butter in skillet; add Worcestershire sauce, basil and tarragon.
Place steaks in skillet. Cook 5 minutes on both sides.
Remove to warmed platter.
Cover with foil.
Place mushrooms in skillet.
Add wine, salt and pepper.
Saute until mushrooms are cooked.
In a small bowl, toss cheese with flour and stir in with mushrooms.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over steaks.
Great with potatoes (baked) and salad.
This is so easy and great.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, juice and all and sprinkle salt and soda over top of pineapple.
Add the flour and mix real good.
Empty into greased baking dish and sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over top of cake. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a bowl, combine oatmeal, flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix in butter.
Peel, core and slice apples in a greased 8-inch round pan.
Sprinkle topping mixture on apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Slice pepperoni into cubes 1/8-inch thick.
Shred Mozzarella. Preheat oven to 425°.
Using a roller, apply flour on surface. Roll dough into a diamond shape; 6 x 6-inch wide, starting at the smallest point.
Add pepperoni and Mozzarella (small portions at a time).
Roll over and continue adding, then rolling, pinching each end.
After roll is completed spread egg white over roll with paper towel.
Bake on cookie sheet, 15 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: round steak bake
directions: Place steak on foil and sprinkle soup mix on steak. Place potatoes evenly over steak and pour mushrooms with liquid over potatoes and steak. Wrap foil tightly. Bake 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice steak in narrow strips.
Brown steak in 2 tablespoons oil.
Combine with garlic, salt, pepper, soy sauce and sugar for 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot on low.
Turn to high and add vegetables. Dissolve 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water. Stir into pot.
Cook on high 15 to 20 minutes or until thickened. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken fajita sandwiches
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic, cumin and red pepper seasoning in medium-size bowl.
Add chicken.
Refrigerate covered for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: almond potato puffs
directions: Combine the water and butter in small saucepan and bring to boil over high heat.
Remove from heat; add flour, all at once, and beat until smooth.
Add egg, blending thoroughly.
Let cool. Add potatoes to flour-egg mixture and blend well.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Flour hands lightly, shape mixture into tablespoon-size balls.
Roll balls in chopped nuts.
Pour oil into a deep fryer or large saucepan and heat to 375°.
Fry balls in batches until golden, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice and dissolve Jell-O.
Stir well.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix well and pour into Jell-O mold.
Chill.

title: pork chops and kraut
directions: In
casserole
dish,
arrange
pork
chops
in a single layer. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover pork chops with layer of sauerkraut.
Cover
casserole with aluminum foil.
Bake in slow oven, 200°, for 3 to 4 hours or until chops are fork-tender.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours. (You may chill overnight or longer.)
Roll in balls the size of a small walnut.
Dip the tops of the balls in the 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon mixture and place about 3-inches apart on greased (sprayed) cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: butterscotch crunch squares(frozen dessert)
directions: Combine flour, oats, and sugar.
Cut in butter until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Pat mix into 13 x 9 inch pan and bake in a 400 degree oven for 15 minutes.
Stir while warm to crumble and then cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Place sliced strawberries in jello; congeal overnight.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and pineapple.
Spread over jello.
Top with chopped pecans.
Chill again until firm.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add nuts. Melt butter and mix in brown sugar, egg, and vanilla. Add flour mixture to butter mixture and mix well. Spread in square baking pan and sprinkle chips on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Line aluminum foil with a single layer of crackers. In a saucepan combine margarine with brown sugar. Stir and let come to a low boil. Let mixture low boil for about 1-2 minutes. Pour mixture over the crackers. Quickly and carefully spread. Bake 5 minutes at 400 degrees. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked mixture. Refrigerate. When very cool, break apart. Remove from foil.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese together with mixer.
Blend in brown sugar and Kahlua.
Stir in peanuts and chill.
Serve with fresh fruit: apple and pear wedges, strawberries or banana chunks.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak (cut into thin slices) in hot oil.
Remove meat.
Cook onion and mushrooms until golden.
Stir remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Return meat to pan.
Simmer about 1 hour, or until tender.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Heat to almost boiling.
Serve over wild rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: spanish sauce
directions: Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: cold pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on large baking sheet and bake according to directions.
Cool.
Spread rest of ingredients on cooled crust. Add shredded cheese, green pepper and onion.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: donna's dessert
directions: Break angel food into pieces and place in bottom of 15 x 12-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth, then add Cool Whip.
Make 3 packages Jell-O with 2 1/2 cups boiling water, adding frozen berries after Jell-O is dissolved.

title: "sean's favorite" cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Layer with cranberries and apple. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Beat egg until thick; slowly add 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and melted butter until blended well. Pour egg mixture over cranberry mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and chill several hours before serving. Excellent as stuffing in a loaf of pumpernickel bread.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Pour 2 cups batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan; bake 15 minutes.
In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well.
Spread caramel over cake.
Spread remaining batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.

title: crumb-coated chicken
directions: In small bowl beat together eggs, butter and salt.
In shallow dish place crumbs.
Coat chicken with crumbs, then egg mixture and crumbs again.
In 2 qt. oblong glass baking dish arrange chicken with meatiest pieces to outside edges of dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave:
13 to 16 minutes.
Power level:
high (10)

title: potato salad
directions: Cut up potatoes and boil.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar and oil to warm potatoes.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: stew beef with gravy
directions: Roll stew beef in flour.
Heat oil and brown stew beef.
When well browned, place in saucepan and add Worcestershire sauce and Texas Pete.
Cover with water.
Cover and simmer until tender. Delicious served with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Mix vegetables with kraut.
Pour liquid over mixture.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Keeps a long time.

title: marinated mushrooms and veggies
directions: In saucepan, combine vinegar, oil, onion, garlic, 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, basil, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour hot marinade over veggies.
Stir; chill several hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain before serving.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 7 cups.
Great Thanksgiving dish.

title: fruit-cookie pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough and place on a baking pan.
Bake according to pkg directions.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together and spread over cookie, slice fruit and layer on top of cheese mixture.
Garnish with pecans and cool whip.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat margarine until smooth.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together.
Slowly add flour until all ingredients are blended well.
Add sour cream and blend.
Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then turn down to 300° and bake for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: quick green beans and potatoes
directions: Empty beans into crock-pot.
Add drained potatoes, onion and bacon.
Cook on high for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf deluxe
directions: Mix together and form a loaf.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix all together, except sour cream and sugar.
Now add sour cream and sugar.
Mix well and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into a buttered dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover sweet potato mixture with marshmallows.
Put back in oven long enough to brown and melt marshmallows.

title: ice cream sodas
directions: Place flavoring or fruit in a tall glass; add sugar.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, pumpkin and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Heat sugar, salt, oil and vinegar until mixture boils and turns clear (until sugar melts).
Pour over cabbage mixture; do not stir.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Blend shortening and sugar, then add eggs and molasses.
Mix flour, salt, soda and spices. Add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and chill 25 to 30 minutes. Roll into balls and dip top into sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Place 1 drop of water on top of sugar on each cookie. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: In 3-quart casserole snip bacon into 1 inch pieces.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave at High (10) 2 to 3 minutes, until crisp.
With slotted spoon, place bacon on paper towels to drain. To bacon drippings add vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and tarragon. Microwave at High (10) 2 to 3 minutes, until mixture boils.
Stir in celery and onion.
Gradually add spinach to hot dressing, tossing to coat each piece.
Add crumbled bacon, orange segments and cashews.
Toss again lightly.
Serve immediately.
Total Microwave Cooking Time:
4 to 6 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook
potatoes in skin and cool.
Remove skin and shred coarsely.
Mix
potatoes and cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or large casserole.
Cook onion in 1/4 cup butter until soft. Mix with
sour cream and celery soup.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin; sift together next six ingredients.
Gradually beat into first mixture; stir in cherries and nuts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate and paraffin until smooth. Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over low heat. Cool slightly.
Dip (toothpick works best) peanut butter balls into chocolate and paraffin.
Place on waxed paper to harden.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and spread over cooked pork roast, ribs, chicken or whatever you wish to barbecue.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: stripe-it-rich-cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes once down through the cake to the pan with the round handle of a wooden spoon.
Holes should be 1-inch apart.
If you don't have wooden spoon, you may use a plastic drinking straw using a turning motion to make large holes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes 15 minutes and drain.
Cool and cube.
Chop onion.
Cut up Velveeta cheese.
Mix with mayonnaise and cubed potatoes.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Spread mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip ambrosino
directions: Cream together with a fork cream cheese and cottage cheese until blended.
Layer mixture in bottom of a glass pie plate or serving bowl/plate.
Add layer of taco sauce, vegetables and Cheddar.
Alternate layers until supplies are exhausted. Finish with Cheddar and garnish with parsley.
Serve with taco chips to scoop.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; this mixture should drain overnight in a colander in the refrigerator.
Dispose of juice.
Mix cranberry mixture with grapes and pecans.
Beat 1/2 pint of whipping cream; add sugar to taste.
Mix with cranberries.
Makes a festive salad.
Delicious when served with turkey.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the oleo or butter and sugar together until creamy by hand or mixer.
Add the eggs, cream of tartar, vanilla and soda.
Mix until well blended.
Add the flour, one cup at a time, blending well after each addition.
Roll into small balls and press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes in a heavy pan or 10 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Make sure the cookie sheets are cool and cleaned before putting more cookies on them. The dough may be chilled for awhile or overnight to make it easier to handle.

title: spring breakfast strata
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs; add milk, mustard, basil and salt. Gently stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or over night.
Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, celery seed, pepper, sugar, vinegar, sour cream and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Mix well, chill.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until done and add salt while cooking. When tender, drain all water off of potatoes; add butter, mustard and mayonnaise. Mix with mixer on low speed. Add remaining chopped boiled eggs, diced onion and diced dill pickles. Stir together and really enjoy.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by sifting.
Blend flour and salt; stir into butter mixture. Mix in nuts. Chill at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes while still warm.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt the Hershey bar over low heat.
Blend into Cool Whip. Pour mixture into the pie crust.
Put in refrigerator and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: mackerel potato cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients except fat.
Put fat in pan and drop cakes in hot pan.
Fry.

title: creamy shrimp dip
directions: Cut shrimp into halves or fourths.
Cover and refrigerate. Mix cream cheese, sour cream and lemon juice until smooth.
Add onions and seasonings; mix well.
Stir in shrimp and gradually add mayonnaise to give good dipping consistency.
Cover and chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers and sturdy chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, rice and celery.
Add soup, mayonnaise, onions and water chestnuts.
Put in a large uncovered casserole.
Top with corn flakes that have been mixed with 1/2 stick melted margarine and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.
Can be frozen.
Freeze unbaked.
Bring to room temperature before baking.

title: ashley's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in slow oven at 275° for about an hour.

title: zucchini bread(julie's favorite)
directions: Beat eggs until
light	and
fluffy.
Add
oil,
sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix	lightly,
but well.
Add remaining ingredients, mix until blended.
Add nuts.	Put in greased and floured loaf pans.	Makes 2.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Mix cake mix (dry), melted butter, nuts and 1/3 cup Pet milk. Stir by hand.
Put 1/2 mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake for 6 minutes at 350° (ungreased).
Combine caramel and 1/3 cup milk. Melt in double boiler.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked mix. Pour melted caramel over chocolate chips.
Pour remainder of cake dough over mix.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pie crust supreme
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening. Add water, vinegar and egg all at once to the dry ingredients.
Mix. Roll as usual.

title: s'more gorp
directions: In a large bag, mix the ingredients.
Then shake well.
