This recipe gives you the same S'more flavor without the trouble of roasting the marshmallows and other things.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Measure pecans in a small bowl.
Mix vinegar and sugar; pour over pecans and stir to coat thoroughly.
Let stand 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Place pecans in a shallow baking dish and bake in a 300° oven for 10 minutes.
Add melted butter to pecans, stir and allow to bake for another 5 minutes.

title: coconut pecan balls
directions: Mix sugar, pecans, coconut.
Add milk, margarine.
Mix and roll into balls.
Refrigerate to harden.
Melt chocolate and wax in double boiler or on
very low heat.
Dip each ball and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: butter rolls
directions: Use your favorite biscuit dough.
Roll out like for jelly roll.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut butter up; put on top.
Roll up in rolls; prick with fork.
Put rolls in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex bowl. Pour milk over rolls; milk should almost cover rolls.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.
Makes about 3 rolls.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar, butter, egg and vanilla in a bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and peanut butter chips.
Drop spoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 to 13 minutes or until cookies are golden.
Cool.

title: strawberries(using dry jello)
directions: Combine milk, coconut, one box of jello, almonds, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well, then hand-shape to form strawberries.
Roll berries in other box of jello to coat thoroughly.
Set to dry. Pipe green icing on berries to form leaf and stems.

title: bea's hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and oleo.
Add flour and paprika.
Take 1 teaspoon of the mixture and wrap around an olive.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be prepared early and frozen before baking.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cover and cook over very low heat for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender and milk is absorbed.
Stir mixture occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot rice mixture into egg mixture.
Add remaining egg mixture to remaining rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Serve warm or cold with fruit or raisins.

title: no bake snow drop cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar very gradually; beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons in mounds on baking sheet.
Place in a 350° oven and turn oven off.
Leave 3 hours to overnight.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add the jello and mix well (any flavor may be used).
Add sugar with rhubarb.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Let boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add next 5 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Drop on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chip dip
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese melted.
Serve with Doritos or other chips.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Mix flour with cold milk until there are no lumps.
Add eggs, salt, pepper and cheese.
Add onion and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 minutes until brown, bake at 350 degrees.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers.
In punch bowl, crumble 1st layer of cake.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix prepared cheese cake fillings and packages of cream cheese together and set aside.
Take melted margarine and pour over both crusts.
Put
one
half
of
the
margarine
on each crust.
Put a cup of
pecans in the bottom of each crust, then divide the cheese cake
and
cream
cheese mixture between the two pies.
Pour over the pecans.
Pour cherry pie filling over each pie, then top with Cool Whip.	Chill and serve.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, then add sugar and egg.
Stir in one-half of the flour, then the milk and then the remaining flour.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and chopped onion in oil.
Whip cottage cheese with basil and oregano in blender. Place alternating layers of zucchini, cottage cheese and tomatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown chops.
Drain on absorbent paper.
In buttered, oblong baking dish, arrange chops, potatoes and mushrooms on top.
In a small bowl, combine water and soup mix.
Pour over other ingredients in baking dish.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put tater tots in bottom of pan. Brown ground chuck, drain. Put over
tots. Pour soup in layers over ground chuck in any order. Spread cheese and put over soup. Bake at 350 degrees, until bubbly about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite-size pieces. Cut off tough outer layer of stalks and chop the tender part into small pieces.
You need 8 cups of broccoli.
(Do this the day before and store in plastic bag.)
Saute bacon until crisp.
Slice onion lengthwise.
In large bowl, combine the broccoli, onion and raisins and bacon.
In small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Combine dressing with the vegetables; refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with sunflower seeds.

title: quick taco salad
directions: Step 1:
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain.
Remove from skillet.
Set aside.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Double recipe makes 3 pies.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Extract juice from strawberries.
Combine dry ingredients for cake, then add others.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: italian delight(large portion)
directions: Take the cubed steak and set it into the pan (with Crisco) on medium-low.
While steak is cooking, chop the veggies into fine pieces and place them in a bowl (with the cheese).
When the meat is done, put it in with the veggies.
Put the whole jar of Ragu into the pan (simmer with a little bit of water).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add egg and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into first mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half and roll out on lightly floured pastry sheet.
Roll thin but thick enough to pick up the design in the cookie cutters.
Dip cutter in flour before each cutting.
Cut as many cookies from each rolling as possible.
The least amount of working with the dough gives the best cookie.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes or until delicately golden.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Dissolve all ingredients, except beets; bring to boil.
Add diced or sliced beets until warm.
Put in sterile bottles and seal.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cornstarch, jello, lemon juice and water. Cook until it becomes thick, stirring occasionally.
Allow to cool.
Put berries in pie shell; pour thickened mixture on top. Chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping; garnish with halves or whole berries.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, coarsely crumble crackers to cover bottom of dish.
Layer asparagus over crackers; slice Velveeta cheese and layer over asparagus, then cover with about 1/2 can of mushroom soup.
Alternate layers until all ingredients are used.
End with a fine layer of cracker crumbs on top.
For more moisture, you can add 1 or 2 tablespoons of the juice from the asparagus.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg
whites
stiff
and add sugar; then add baking powder, vanilla, pecans and crackers.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake
at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool prepare Dream Whip
as directed on box.
Mix with cream cheese and pineapple
and
spread
over
dessert;
refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients in bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Add chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 8 to 10 hours. Turn at least once in marinade.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste with pan juices and serve over rice.

title: apricot-blueberry coffee cake(a favorite of family and friends)
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream; beat well by hand; add blueberries and apricots.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Pour 1/2 of the cake mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Add the remaining cake mixture, then the remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: crab treats
directions: Combine cheese, milk, onion, Worcestershire, lemon juice and spices.
Stir in crab.
Halve English muffins with a fork.
Cut halves into fourths and pile each wedge high with crab mixture. Place on baking sheet; dust with paprika and broil until lightly browned and bubbly.
Makes about 40.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together first three ingredients, then add the coconut, pecans and raisins.
Stir well, then add vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: ham sauce
directions: Blend cornstarch, mustard and salt into ham drippings.
Add water, sugar and raisins.
Cook and stir until clear and slightly thickened.
Blend into vinegar and lemon juice.
Makes 3 cups.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Make 24 hours before serving.
Use large casserole or large glass pan.
Shred or tear lettuce into dish, approximately 1/3 full.
Layer on top of the following (do not stir): green peas, green pepper, celery, red onion.
Frost entire top with the following mixture:
mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Right before serving, sprinkle with bacon.

title: glazed waverly crackers
directions: Line cookie sheet, 12 x 16-inch, with Waverly crackers and sprinkle about 1/2 cup pecans on top of crackers.
Boil sugar and oleo for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove crackers from cookie sheet while still hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat peanut butter, cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add sugar and milk; fold in whipped topping. Pour into the crust. Cover and freeze for at least 4 hours. Remove from the freezer just before serving. Garnish with peanuts and chocolate curls if desired. Yield: 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together with a whisk.
Brush on meats or poultry last 20 minutes of cooking or grilling.

title: kim's corned beef hash
directions: Wash and peel potatoes, chop into wedges and place in microwave safe dish. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Add butter to potatoes last few minutes in microwave. Cook bacon, remove from grease and brown onions. Add to potatoes along with corned beef, place on top and do not stir. Cook until done.

title: play dough
directions: Put in saucepan the flour, salt, cream of tartar and cooking oil. Add the boiling water. Cook until it sticks together and is doughy.

title: cioppino
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
In a large saucepan, cook green onion, onion and garlic in hot oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, wine, parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add fish, shrimp and undrained clams.
Bring just to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
This stew is delicious on its own or over rice.
Serve with salad and warm bread.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together real good, then pour in ice cream freezer. Freeze as you would ice cream.

title: best-ever egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in medium saucepan.
Slowly beat in two (2) cups of the milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until thermometer registers 150°F. or mixture coats the back of a metal spoon.
Remove from heat;
strain into pitcher.
Stir in remaining milk, Jim Beam Bourbon, vanilla and nutmeg.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with additional nutmeg.

title: crescent roll casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning and tomato sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 can of rolls onto bottom of pan.
Spread hamburger mixture on top of rolls. Sprinkle both kinds of cheese on top, then top with second can of rolls.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and slice eggplant. Cook in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients except cheese slices. Place in a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Arrange cheese slices on top and bake an additional 20 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: gold kist pecan pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add slightly beaten eggs and other ingredients.
When all is blended, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on lower shelf of oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Top each breast with cheese slice; set aside.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and drizzle with butter.
Bake chicken at 350° for 150 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Soak cereal in warm milk for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs with fork; add sugar to taste.
Add salt, vanilla and cereal/milk mixture. Spoon into a buttered 5 cup casserole dish.
If desired, sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Set casserole into a pan partly filled with water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Stir at least twice during the first 20 minutes of baking.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve warm or chilled.
Store leftover pudding in refrigerator.

title: mexican salad
directions: Pinch lettuce in small pieces.
Combine all other ingredients except Fritos.
Add them just before serving.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place all
ingredients
in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in ungreased, 9 x 5
x 3-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar. Set aside. Mix together pudding and milk until smooth.
Mix in whipped topping.
Mix in cream cheese mixture.
Alternate layers of the crushed cookies and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with cookies.
Put in refrigerator or freeze until firm.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts. Makes 2 or more pies!

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple.
Pour into oiled mold.
(Halved works well.)

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish or pan with graham crackers. Mix pudding according to directions on box and spread over crackers.
Spread Cool Whip over that and put in refrigerator until pudding sets.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: italian string beans
directions: Cook beans until partially tender; drain and saute in olive oil, 1 clove garlic and oregano.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: In a 5-quart pot, heat oil.
Add chicken and saute until meat is not pink.
Add water, mushrooms, cabbage, bamboo shoots and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour. In small bowl, dissolve cornstarch and stir with fork until smooth.
Stir into soup.
Add vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper. Stir soup until slightly thickened and enjoy.
Unused soup can be frozen for a quick meal anytime.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package and drain.
Combine tuna, soup, onion, vinegar, milk and Cheddar cheese in a bowl.
Mix well. Stir in noodles. Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie de kahlua
directions: Dot shell with Kahlua and set aside.
Slightly beat egg yolks in top of a double boiler.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Place over simmering water.
Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Melt chocolate with 1/4 cup water in a small saucepan.
Stir melted chocolate
mixture into egg yolks.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to thickened chocolate mixture.
Stir well and remove from heat.
Add Kahlua.
Place pan with mixture in a bowl of ice water to cool. In small bowl, beat cream with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff. In another small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
When chocolate mixture begins to thicken, fold in half of the whipped cream, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Refrigerate remaining whipped cream.
Turn chocolate mixture into pie shell, chill.
Top pie with remaining whipped cream and almonds.
Makes one 9 inch pie.

title: green rice
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Toss rice and spinach together. Add eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion. Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle butter and cheese over rice. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes to soften.

title: good green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes until bacon pieces are done.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, sausage, onion and garlic.
Drain. Add next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti as package directs.
Drain.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti.
Pass the Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except walnuts, in a large bowl. Microwave at Medium (50% power) until chocolate chips are melted (about 3 to 5 minutes), stirring once or twice during cooking. Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased (8 x 8-inch) square baking dish.
Refrigerate until set (overnight if possible).

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Brown the butter; add flour, then milk.
Stir and cook until smooth.
Add cheese and mushroom soup and stir until melted.
Pour over beans.
Heat.

title: electric frypan swiss steak
directions: On a breadboard, pound flour into both sides of steak; cut into serving pieces until flour is absorbed.
Preheat frypan to 360°. Add fat and onions; saute until golden in color, about 3 minutes. Remove from fat.
Change frypan setting to 400° and add a tablespoon of fat.
Then brown steak on both sides, about 10 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle browned meat with salt and pepper; add the sauteed onions, garlic, celery, tomatoes and pepper slices.
Cover and set frypan at 220°.
Simmer until the meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley when serving.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine cheese, dates and 1/2 cup pecans.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Serve with apple wedges or gingersnaps.
Makes 2 cups.

title: aunt lettie's pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar gradually.
Put in refrigerator.
Cream butter and add remainder of sugar.
Beat at low speed.
Add 2 egg yolks at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring and fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased steeple pan.
Bake 1 3/4 hours in a 300° oven.

title: sauerbraten patties
directions: Soften bread in water.
Add beef, onion, egg, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Form into patties.
Brown on both sides in butter in heavy skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic rosemary chicken
directions: Wash chicken. Push garlic and rosemary under skin and in cavity. Cook in Brown N Bag
1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook until cheese is melted.
Keep on warmer and serve with Doritos or other chips.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut up chicken and put in casserole.
Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Stir whipping cream and sugar together well.
Cook 7 minutes. Stir well, then cook 7 more minutes.
Remove and add butter and pecans.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla (optional), then drop on wax paper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream shortening, butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a loaf pan, greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: savory chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breast in shallow baking dish.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix evenly over milk and soup mixture.
Drizzle melted oleo over stuffing.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and continue baking for 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: raisin-filled apples
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Peel off a strip around top of apples.
Place apples in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; fill centers with nut mixture.
Microcook, covered, until tender, 5 to 6 minutes; give dish a half turn twice.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until hamburger is brown and crumbly.
Drain off excess fat.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until carrots are tender at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, powdered sugar and orange juice and roll in small balls.
Then roll these in the coconut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, salt and raisins.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add margarine.
Mix soda and vinegar together and add to mixture.
This dough will be stiff, but mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, depending on how crisp or soft you like them.

title: butternut squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and discard seeds.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices crosswise and remove peel. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Heat orange juice in microwave dish. Dissolve candy in the orange juice.
Pour over squash. Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Place liquid from baking pan into small saucepan and boil until thick.
Pour over squash. Yields 4 servings.
Has 150 calories, fat free.

title: champagne salad(frozen)
directions: Fold in fruit and nuts with mixture.
Freeze in Pyrex dish. Cut into squares.
Fills a 7 x 11-inch dish.

title: chocolate buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour a Bundt pan or tube pan. In large bowl, cream together the butter, shortening, and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. In another bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, salt, and cocoa. Stir to mix.

Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk. Add vanilla and mix well. Stir in walnuts. Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for about 1 hour 10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. After the cake has cooled slightly in the pan, turn it out onto a cake plate.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture.
Form into tiny balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make crisscross.
Dough may also be rolled and cut, if desired.
Bake in moderated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, sausage and onion on low heat; add other ingredients.
Cook in a large pot.
Serve with nacho chips.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix dry ingredients into wet ingredients. Spread 1/2 batter into bottom of 9 x 13 greased baking pan. Spoon pie filling over batter. Drizzle remaining batter over pie filling. Before baking, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and Tabasco sauce.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll ham slices and refrigerate overnight.
Slice in one-inch pinwheels after chilled thoroughly.
Garnish with fresh parsley and serve.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook meat and onion until brown; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat mixture.
Add chilies.
Cut tortillas into thirds.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer salsa, meat, cheese and tortillas in that order.
End with layer of tortillas topped with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 5.

title: mom's dandelion wine
directions: Gather 1 peck dandelion heads.
Do not collect from an area sprayed with pesticides or herbicides.
Wash to remove bugs. Combine dandelion heads with boiling water in a large container. Let the flower heads steep for 24 hours.
Strain the juice.
To the juice, add sugar, yeast and fruit.
The amount of fruit can vary, depending on the flavor you want.
Set it in a warm, dark area to ferment.
Do not stir.
Keep mixture quiet for about 2 weeks.
When the mixture reaches the desired potency, siphon off and filter through cheesecloth.
Refrigerate.
It's ready!

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour and sugar.
Add potatoes, eggs, corn syrup, nutmeg, salt, butter and evaporated milk.
Beat well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: smoked salmon rolls
directions: Blend softened cheese with capers.
Spread on salmon.
Roll, jelly-roll fashion.
Chill.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Serve on cocktail picks.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix Crisco or oleo, powdered sweetener, milk, almond, vanilla and eggs together and add flour, baking powder and nuts.
Make into logs and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° until light brown.
They do not brown like cookies with sugar.
Can also add coconut and substitute unsweetened orange juice for the milk.
Keep in refrigerator.
(Thirteen calories per cookie.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake batter using first 8 ingredients.
Melt 1/3 cup butter and brown sugar in cake pan (10 to 12-inch) or an iron skillet.
Put the pineapple in the pan and place a cherry in the center of each pineapple slice if you wish.
Then cover with cake batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Loosen cake from sides of pan and invert on large plate.
Serve warm or cold, plain or with whipped cream.

title: gone all afternoon stew
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes turning once.

title: turkey chili
directions: In large heavy pot, brown turkey; pour off any excess fat. Add onion, green pepper and garlic; cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans, water, tomatoes, tomato paste, chili powder, oregano, cumin and red pepper; cover.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain off fat.
Add soup, beans, green chilies, chili powder, salt and pepper; simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or with crackers.

title: crock pot pepper roast
directions: Place about 5 or 6 peppers in bottom of pot.
Put roast on top.
Pour remaining peppers and the juice on top.	Cook on low all day while you are at work.
You could also put on before bed and allow to cook all night.
Refrigerate in the morning.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown the steak.
Mix the remaining ingredients and put on top of the steak.
Bake.

title: beatnik cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Roll chicken in a mixture of flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle with Parmesan and then Mozzarella.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with spaghetti or vermicelli.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Dip into boiling water the peaches.
Plunge peaches into cold water.
Slip off skins. Cut in half.
Discard pits.
Press peaches through sieve or food mill into mixing bowl.
Stir in 1 tablespoon lemon juice and the sugar.

Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine the heavy cream, vanilla, almond extract and salt. Stir into peach mixture. Fill freezer container 2/3 full of mixture. Cover tightly. Set in freezer tub and freeze until firm.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Finish cooling before adding icing.

title: sauce for fresh fruit
directions: Place beaten egg in top of double boiler and add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add butter and pineapple juice.
Cook over water until smooth and thickened.
Cool, then add Dream Whip or whipping cream.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel eggplant and cook in boiling water 7 to 10 minutes. Drain and season with dash of onion powder and dill.
Mix remaining ingredients with 1/3 cup cracker crumbs and combine with eggplant.
Put in 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter and dash of paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: famous lemon pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and lemon juice in pan.
Separate 3 yolks from egg whites, set the whites aside.
Add egg yolks to lemon mixture and stir, then add boiling water and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff peaks form for topping.
Spread onto pie and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until topping is golden brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs slightly.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8-inch dish in a preheated 375° oven. Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Stir into melted margarine.
Top with cherries and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fiesta onion salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with vegetables, fish, chicken or tortilla chips.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: rudy's farm holiday dressing
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cook onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients together; dump in sausage, onion, oleo and celery.
Stuff a 14 to 20 pound bird or dressing may be baked in pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Feeds a hungry family!!

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Pour and press into lightly greased cake pan.
Mix pumpkin, 2 eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and milk.
Pour over crust mix.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: spatini meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, Spatini, cold water and bread crumbs.
Shape into meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in bowl as listed.
Let sit 8 hours overnight in refrigerator.

title: north rim rolls(grand canyon)
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Refrigerate overnight. Roll out dough.
Cut or shape as desired.
Let rise at least an hour.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue meatball bites
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and poultry seasoning. Shape into about 2 dozen 1 1/2-inch balls. Brown balls slowly in a lightly oiled skillet over medium-high heat. Pour off excess fat.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients together with nuts, dates and cut cherries.
Mix well.
Crush corn flakes into fine crumbs.
Shape dough into balls using 1 level tablespoon dough each.
Roll balls into crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top each with 1/4 cherry.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until lightly brown. Yield:
6 dozen 2-inch diameter cookies.

title: applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add oats and blend well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sensational celery
directions: Cook celery in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Drain water chestnuts; reserve liquid.
Slice water chestnuts.
Drain mushrooms and reserve liquid.
Mix celery, water chestnuts, almonds and mushrooms.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add reserved liquids, milk and broth; cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in celery mixture; pour into casserole.
Top with crumbs; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until bubbly and brown.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add soda and vinegar, then vanilla and flour.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for about 15 minutes at 300°.

title: hot sauce
directions: Place tomatoes with juice in bowl, mash tomatoes to desired consistency.
Place jalapenos, onion and garlic in food processor and chop.
In skillet, over low heat, place vinegar, oil and jalapeno mixture until warm to touch (do not boil).
Sprinkle with salt several times.
Add tomatoes, stir well.
Place in jars and refrigerate.

title: israeli salad
directions: Dice each vegetable into extremely small pieces.
Add oil, then squeeze in the juice of 1 to 2 lemons depending on your taste.
Add the salt, then add lemon, oil and salt based on how much salad you need.
The salad should be tart and refreshing.

title: chicken enchilada(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix all the ingredients.
Microwave on High for 11 to 13 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn; cook 5 minutes.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine jello, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Chill 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
If you wish, tint sliced almonds with green food coloring and insert in tops of berries to form leaves.
Makes 1 pound, 3 ounces. Very pretty to use among Christmas goodies.

title: coconut cake
directions: In a medium-size bowl, put 1/2 cup of coconut, then add 4 tablespoons sugar and 3/4 cup of warm milk. Stir well until mixed. Poke cake all over with fork and then pour the milk mixture all over cake, then allow to cool and frost with frosting made from Cool Whip, sour cream, 1/4 cup of confectioners sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut. Then top with remaining coconut. Chill until time to serve. Cake needs at least 3 hours to saturate, but overnight in fridge is best.

title: mashed potato hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Peel, cut and boil potatoes.
Mash potatoes.
Add butter and milk; set aside.
Drain green beans.
Combine tomato soup, green beans and browned hamburger in a greased baking dish.
Layer mashed potatoes on top of hamburger mixture.
Spread evenly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes and serve.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 1/2 cups mix (12 to 14 servings).

title: swedish pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: deer roast
directions: You will also need one oven baking bag.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice and cornstarch in saucepan until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and cinnamon.
Pour over apples in large bowl and mix carefully.
Pour into pie crust and cover with second pie crust.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and veggie crescents
directions: Combine spinach or broccoli, cheese spread, bread crumbs and bacon in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Unroll dough
and separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each triangle in half lengthwise so you'll have 32 triangles.
Spread each triangle with about 1 teaspoon of mixture.
Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Whip Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix flour, soda, cream of tartar and pinch of salt.
Combine and drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Spread ingredients in layers (Chili, cheese, Fritos, onion, tamales, cheese then repeat.)

title: grits casserole 2
directions: Cook grits in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Delicious with ham.

title: orange lemonade
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Finely shred enough orange and lemon peel to make 2 tablespoons.
Set aside.
Squeeze juice from the lemons and 1 1/2 cups orange juice. Add juices and peel to the cooled syrup.
If desired, pour over mint sprig, cover and let stand 1 hour.
Strain mixture; pour into jars and cover.
Refrigerate.
To serve, fill glasses or pitcher with ice cubes.
Pour equal amounts of fruit syrup and water over ice.
Stir to combine.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices. Makes 6 cups fruit syrup or 12 (8 ounce) servings of orange-lemonade.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Stir in all ingredients. Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas house fragrance
directions: Mix and bring to boil.
Keep simmering.
(Crock-pot is great.)

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix
sugar
and
cocoa	in microwave-proof bowl.
Place stick of butter in center of dry mix.
Pour milk over.
Do not try to mix!

title: tomato parmesan salad
directions: In a small bowl or jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper; set aside.
In a large salad bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain. Add tomato juice, beans and seasoning mix; set aside. Layer casserole dish with chips, chili, cheese, chips, chili, cheese until all ingredients are used. Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: frozen slush
directions: Mix in order given; put in Tupperware dish.
Put in freezer. Whenever you want a slush, scrape with ice cream scoop.

title: fudge cookie cake
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in large bowl, set aside.
Bring to a boil oleo, water, oil and cocoa, pour over flour mixture and stir until well mixed.
In a small bowl beat the eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Stir into mixture and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch) and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in frypan or pot.
Remove from heat.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: low-fat bran-apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat 12 (2 3/4 inch) muffin tin cups with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, bran and baking soda; set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream sugar, prune puree; beat in egg whites and molasses.
Stir in buttermilk mixture, flour, apple and salt.
Blend thoroughly. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups, dividing equally.
Bake about 20 minutes until pick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool completely.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream the cheese and sour cream and spread on a platter.
Add the taco seasoning to taste.
Chop and spread on the cream cheese mixture: onion, lettuce and tomato.
Spread the Cheddar cheese over the top.
Use real "nachos" or Tostitos with dip.

title: baking dish cobbler
directions: Butter a 9 or 10-inch pie dish at least 1 1/2 inches deep. Place peaches in dish.
Spread bread evenly over peaches.
Mix melted butter, sugar, flour and egg together until well blended. Pour evenly over bread, making sure all bread is covered.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Add water to apples and cook until done.
Add sugar, salt and spices and simmer until jelled.
Refrigerate until used.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Turn off and place pan in oven with peanut butter and Candi-Quick.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: braised bratwurst with spicy mustard sauce
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, with sharp knife, score sausages for even cooking.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook sausages in apple cider until cider evaporates and sausages are browned and heated, turning sausages occasionally.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° in oblong pan until cake falls (or about 45 minutes).
Cool and cut into squares.

title: garden green salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well. Combine lemon juice and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over lettuce mixture.
Toss gently.
Yields
4 servings.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When thickened, add apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juice bubbles through slits.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter, powdered sugar and salt.
Pat in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (don't brown).
Beat the eggs, sugar, flour and lemon juice for 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes more.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Double the recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients in blender. Add 1/2 cup salt. Let stand for 2 hours. Drain dry or squeeze out. Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed. Mix well; pack into jars and seal. Makes 10 pints.

title: funny cake
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar, cocoa and water for a few minutes, then let cool.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour first mixture into unbaked pie crust, then drop second mix by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan roll
directions: Place milk, sugar, and butter in iron skillet and cook over medium heat. Stir until mixture turns brown and gets thick and sugary. Add pecans and vanilla flavoring. Pour into well buttered plate. Cut into squares before it is completely cool.

title: grape finger jello
directions: Soften gelatin in juice and cold water.
Add the boiling water and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares and serve.

title: belgian pie
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1-1/2 teaspoons sugar in warm water; set aside until bubbly.
Beat 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt. Add cream and butter.
Beat.
Add yeast mixture and slowly blend in flour.
Mix well and let stand for 10 minutes.
Divide into 5 or 6 parts.
Form into balls.
Press into greased pans, forming a 1/2 inch ridge around outside of the pan.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Pour rice, prune, poppy seed, apple, cherry or any cake and pastry filling over the center.
Top with Cheese topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cook the bacon in iron skillet until crisp.
Add the onion and peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, together with mixer until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: oriental grilled chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a shallow pan large enough to hold breasts in one layer.
Place breasts in marinade, turning to coat and rubbing marinade into breasts.
Marinate at least one hour and as long as overnight.
Grill chicken over hot coals or under broiler.
Strain marinade, bring it to a boil and serve it with chicken.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 21 g, fat 5 g, calories 186.

title: pork chops au gratin
directions: Brown the pork chops.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and put into large casserole dish.
Place browned pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: soft sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening, add eggs and sour cream. Mix well. Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda. Add to creamed mixture slowly. After well mixed, set overnight in refrigerator. Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut into shapes. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. Frost and decorate.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and cream of tartar in pan.
Add water, food coloring and oil.
Stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Don't worry if globby.
Keep stirring until ball forms in center of pot. Take out and put on floured surface.
Squish and punch a bit (kneading).
Keep in plastic bag or airtight container.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican fiesta pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch square pan or 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Layer half the corn chips, chili, onion and cheese in pan; repeat.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, ReaLime and food coloring (if desired).
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool; chill. Top with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
(Refrigerate leftovers.)

title: "cheaters" mexican bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 baking pan with nonstick spray and line bottom with burritos, which have been cut into thirds. Mix chili and salsa together and pour over burritos. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple chunks in bottom of glass 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix sugar and flour together and sprinkle over pineapple.
Then layer cheese and crushed crackers to form top layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: dilly beans
directions: Trim beans and pack in 4 pint canning jars. Add 1 garlic clove and 1/4 teaspoon cayenne and dill to each jar. Boil salt, water and vinegar. Pour into jars. Cover jars with canning lids. Process 10 minutes. These are great addition to a relish tray and good in Bloody Marys.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Bake 35 minutes in cast-iron pot or medium cast-iron frypan at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Knead 10 times.
Cut and bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Toss rice and spinach together.
Add eggs, milk, worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Sprinkle butter and cheese over rice.
Heat oven to 325°.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all together green beans, peas, corn, celery, onion, pimentos and bell pepper and cover with Italian dressing, oil, vinegar and sugar.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with milk, stirring until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool a few minutes and remove.

title: arame (sea vegetable) and carrots
directions: *Arame is available at the Grainery and at Mellon Produce.

title: mike's ice cream
directions: Combine all.
Leave plain or add whatever fruit desired. Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Delicious!

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut up fruit.
Mix it in a bowl.
Mix 3 teaspoons of plain yogurt and 1 teaspoon of vanilla with fruit.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix bouillon and water.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of a casserole dish.
Chop onion, green pepper and place on top of rice.
Place butter pats on top of green peppers and onion.
Pour bouillon mixture over casserole.
Put chicken on top of rice mixture.
Pour the mushroom soup over the chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ovens can vary, so use your own judgement.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put raw meat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place raw vegetables on top of meat.
Combine salt, sugar, tapioca and pepper; sprinkle evenly over veggies.
Pour juice evenly over top. Cover with heavy duty foil and crimp edges to seal tightly.
Bake at 250 degrees for 5 hours and Don't Peek!

title: cole slaw, frozen
directions: Shred cabbage; add salt and set for 1 hour.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water, celery and mustard seed.
Boil for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Add pepper and carrot to cabbage.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Mix well.
Put in containers and freeze.
Will keep in refrigerator a week or more.

title: quick yellow split pea soup
directions: Bring water with all ingredients to a boil.
Reduce to medium-low.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add rice or barley during last 10 to 20 minutes of cooking.

title: blt macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse in cold water. In a large bowl, combine the macaroni, green onions, tomato and celery. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour over macaroni mixture and toss to coat. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours. Just before serving, add bacon. Yield: 12 servings.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Into a separate bowl, sift the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to zucchini mixture, along with nuts.
Pour into greased muffin tins or use muffin papers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: ground beef basic mix
directions: Melt margarine in 8-quart pan over low flame.
Add ground beef; turn flame to medium and cook until red color disappears. Add onion, celery and green pepper; cook until beef is brown and vegetables are tender.
Add soup, tomato sauce, salt and pepper; cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool and divide equally into 5 freezer containers.
May be thawed and used in a variety of recipes.

title: anise oil cookies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add egg, wine, vanilla and anise oil.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and remaining ingredients and mix together.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Take out and roll out with cookie cutters.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 3 minutes.

title: valley fresh chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Have butcher cut loin chops with a pocket for the stuffing. Brown onion in butter.
Combine with bread crumbs, raisins, salt and seasoning.
Stuff pockets with stuffing.
Place in an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat
on
stove;
season as you wish. Layer the
hamburger,
potatoes and onions in casserole dish. Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hot sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs; beat in sugar.
Beat in flour.
Melt butter in milk and pour over dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch square pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
May frost or serve plain with fruit, such as strawberries.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Mix sugar, egg, flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts and mix well.
Bake in greased pie tin at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until mixture is a light lemon color.
Add flour and mix well. Form dough in 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or lightly browned.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix egg yolks and all other ingredients well.
Spoon into egg whites and chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water and salt.
Melt cheese and margarine together.
Beat eggs.
Finish cup with milk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in large casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° as you would for any meat loaf.
Time depends on thickness of loaf.
Drain juice off as it bakes.
Cabbage will produce extra liquid.

title: lemon snowdrops
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; add extract.
Sift together flour and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well. Roll level teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: delicious bread pudding #1
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in remaining ingredients and stir.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water, about 1-inch deep, and bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Great for holidays!

title: oriental marinade
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour over uncooked fish or meat.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Grill, broil, saute, stir-fry or bake as you desire.
Grilling seems to bring out the best flavors.
Marinade may be heated and thickened with cornstarch and served as a sauce.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos in a blender or food processor.
Mix pudding with 3 cups ice water and set aside.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip and margarine together; then add pudding.
Line a container with 1/2 of the Oreo cookie crumbs.
Pour pudding mixture into crumb-lined container.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Freeze overnight or at least 3 hours.
Take out of the freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fry together butter and onion until brown.
Add flour and stir.
Add canned soup, milk and broccoli.
Simmer 15 minutes or until broccoli is cooked.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese and simmer 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple. Mix all together. Garnish with cherries and pecans. Chill.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Form balls and drop into sauce; cook at least 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese spoon bread
directions: Scald milk in saucepan.
Add cornmeal and cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Mix in sugar and salt.
Mix small amount of hot cornmeal mixture with egg yolks; return to saucepan and mix thoroughly.
Stir in butter and cottage cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually fold in cornmeal mixture.
Pour into baking dish and bake 35 minutes.
Serve with melted butter.

title: cream of potato soup(heart smart)
directions: In medium saucepan over medium to high heat, melt margarine. Add onion and celery.
Cook about 4 minutes or until soft, stirring frequently.
Add potatoes, chicken broth, parsley, thyme, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer about 15 minutes or until potatoes are almost tender.
Add milk.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In blender at medium speed, blend about 1/4 of the mixture at a time until smooth.
Return to saucepan, heat about 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings, about 1 cup each.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Leave fat from bacon in skillet.
Hold ear of corn perpendicular to cutting board.
With sharp knife, slice downward, cutting off tip ends of kernels, then scrape milk out of remaining kernels.
Heat bacon fat in skillet.
Add scraped corn and kernel tips.
Fry lightly for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add enough milk to make creamed corn consistency. Add butter.
Cook another 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in serving dish and sprinkle crushed bacon over all. Serves 6.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add spices and cocoa.
Fold in blackberries.
Batter will be thick.
Spoon batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: crackle snappers
directions: Melt chocolate morsels over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Combine shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg and beat until creamy.
Blend in melted chocolate and corn syrup. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and stir in gradually.
Add nuts and mix well.
Shape into balls using 1 level tablespoonful for each.
Roll balls in about 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: apple or peach crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Will be dry and crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda with sour cream and add to egg mixture.
Add all dry ingredients and orange rind. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir until all is melted.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased or Saran Wrap covered 12-inch pizza pan or smaller plates. Top with red cherries and 1 green for leaf.
Sprinkle with coconut. Melt remaining white bark and shortening.
Drizzle over coconut. Chill 15 minutes in freezer.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and milk in the middle of the pie pan.
Add oil and mix.
Makes a soft ball of dough.
Press to bottom and sides of pan evenly.

title: mother's rice refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add rice to milk, then add the yeast and eggs.
Add about half of the flour and stir until mixed well.
Add enough of remaining flour to make a very stiff dough.
Stir until dough leaves the sides of bowl.
Knead until smooth.
Place dough in large greased bowl.
Brush dough with melted shortening, cover and refrigerate for at least 12 hours. Remove from refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before baking.
Shape, let rise and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes for rolls.
Can be made into loaves and baked at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 2 loaves.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: cinnamon apple jello
directions: Dissolve jello and candy in boiling water.
When cool, stir in lemon juice, applesauce and salt.
Pour into mold.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well blended.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: trout meuniere
directions: Roll trout in seasoned flour.
Heat oil in frypan and add trout which should be gently cooked and browned on both sides. When thoroughly cooked, transfer trout to heated serving platter and keep hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Chill.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Combine dates, raisins, apples and water.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Cool and add remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Add egg topping which consist of 3 egg whites, 1 Tbsp. sugar, and 1/4 tsp. vanilla flavoring whipped together. Place in oven on 325 degrees until topping browns.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk. Stir in sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm.
Pour warm water into bowl. Sprinkle yeast and dissolve. Add milk mixture. Stir half the flour into mixture, then add rest of flour and combine.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead. Put into greased bowl.
Brush with melted shortening.
Cover and let rise 1 hour and 20 minutes. Punch down. Divide into 2 equal parts.
Knead.
Place in loaf pan.
Let rise 55 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: gin punch
directions: Pour over block of ice in a large punch bowl. Garnish with slices of orange and lemon.

title: white trash
directions: Mix cereal, raisins and peanuts in a large container.
Over low heat, melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate morsels, stirring well.
Remove from stove and cool; pour over cereal mixture and mix well.
Place mixture in large paper bag; pour in confectioners sugar and shake until it is coated.
Store in an airtight container.
Enough for a crowd.

title: sesame loaf
directions: Saute onions and celery in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Blend sunflower seeds and sesame seed.
In bowl, mix together the oatmeal, blended seed, pecan meal, yeast, onion powder, garlic powder, Soy Supreme, bread crumbs, then add soy sauce, onions and celery.
Add water; mix well.
Bake in sprayed baking dish at 325° for 60 minutes until brown.
Serve with Creamy Cashew Gravy.

title: applesauce nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and mix thoroughly. Sift flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Add applesauce, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: berry whirl
directions: Combine the strawberries, pineapple, raspberries and limeade concentrate in a blender container or food processor. Process until smooth. Pour into 2 goblets. Serve immediately.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured pans, about 1 hour, in 350° oven.

title: orange-clove dried tea mix
directions: Dry peel in 200° oven.
Store in airtight jar.

title: mushroom-chicken cutlets
directions: Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and garlic salt.
Mix eggs and water together.
Dip each chicken cutlet into egg mixture, then into crumb mixture.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown cutlets on each side until golden brown.
Remove to flat baking dish.
Saute mushrooms briefly in same skillet; spoon over cutlets.
Combine melted butter and lemon juice; pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice in large mixing bowl.
Make a deep well in center.
Add pumpkin, eggs, oil, water, pecans and raisins.
Mix just enough to moisten all ingredients.

title: stanley surprise
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Bake at 400° until bubbles appear, about 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make dough stiff enough to drop from a teaspoon into hot deep fat.
Cook until brown and drain on paper towels.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Remove chicken and saute onions and garlic until soft.
Add chicken and 20 cups of water.
Bring to a boil and add salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Add rice.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat to a simmer. Stir twice while cooking.
Cook until water is absorbed and chicken is tender.
Yields 24 servings.

title: uncooked, fresh peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, sugar and lemon juice; let stand for 1 hour. Drain and measure 1 cup syrup.
Add cornstarch to syrup and blend. Cook over low heat until thick.
Add salt, butter and flavoring; cool.
Put peaches in shell.
Cover with sauce.
Serve with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: apple casserole
directions: Combine cheese, flour, margarine and sugar.
Mix until creamy. Drain apples and pour into baking dish.
Spread cheese mixture over top.
Pour canned milk over the top of this.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° or until well browned.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Spread over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and enjoy.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In a skillet, cook chicken, onion, carrot and garlic in butter until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.

title: aunt lena's chocolate topping
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add hot water first before cream; cook for 10 minutes at boil.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; beat with mixer until cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, cheese and 1/2 the eggs together.
Gently toss with asparagus.
Top with remaining eggs and a little more cheese, crackers and a few pats of butter.
Bake at 375° until hot and bubbly.

title: hot choco-mallow mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in marshmallows. Store in an airtight container with these serving instructions: Combine 1/4 cup mix and 6 ounces boiling water in a mug.
Stir and serve.

title: bagna cauda(northern italian antipasto)
directions: Heat butter or margarine and olive oil in saucepan.
Add anchovy and garlic.
Cook on low heat, stirring constantly (if using fillets, ensure they dissolve to a paste).
Transfer to a fondue pot over fondue burner.

title: slim jim chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in Dutch oven; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 1 to 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf. Serve hot.
Freezes well.
Can use crock-pot.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings with 156 calories each.

title: molded white bean pate
directions: Place drained kidney beans in a medium bowl and mash thoroughly with a fork.
Saute garlic in olive oil until lightly golden, about 30 seconds.
Do not let it brown.
Mix the garlic and the beans and all other ingredients except 1 tablespoon parsley.

title: aunt mary's fruit punch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients real good.
Then, add the recommended amount of water for each can of orange juice and mix well.
After this, I usually put 1 quart of water and 1 cup of sugar and then stir and taste.
I continue putting 1 quart of water and then some sugar (doesn't have to be a cup each time, maybe 1/2 cup) and taste each time until I get it to taste like I want it.
Everyone has their own taste.

title: pinwheel date cookies
directions: To prepare filling, cook brown sugar, water and dates for 5 minutes, then add nuts.
Allow to cool.
To prepare dough, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then salt and flour, mixing until dough like.
Roll out dough and spread on the filling as for jelly rolls.
Roll up, chill, slice and bake at 400° until done.

title: fabulous fruit salad
directions: All fruits must be fresh, not canned or frozen.
Prepare and slice all fruit into bite size pieces.
Mix instant pudding mix powder (not prepared) with fruit and refrigerate overnight in sealed bowl.
Before serving the next day, toss lightly, mixing thoroughly.
The juice and pudding mix make a nice fruit pudding.

title: newport seafood bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasonings.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Cook fish; skin, bone and cut in pieces.
Add fish, shrimp, lobster and sherry to sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Toss crumbs with margarine; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Place caramels and water in double boiler and stir to dissolve.
Pur over pecans.
Make in flat round balls.
Put on buttered platter and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Combine chicken and 1/3 cheese soup.
Roll up in crescent rolls.
Heat remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture on jelly roll pan.
Arrange rolls on top of mixture and pour remaining soup mixture on triangles.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: dream bars
directions: Combine all ingredients with pastry blender or in food processor until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pita bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and add more flour if necessary.
Make into 2 balls.
Knead each ball, then divide into 12 smaller balls. Cover.
Let rise about 30 to 40 minutes.
Flatten balls to about 6 inches in diameter with rolling pin on a lightly floured board. Cover and let rise slightly.
Flip the dough so that the bottom side of the bread dough is on the top side of baking sheets. Preheat oven as hot as it bakes.
Place sheet on lowest rack.
Bake about 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 24 pita breads.

title: country fair corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease well 14 corn stick molds.
Place in oven while preparing batter.
In large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In small skillet, add oil and cook pepper and onions until tender.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in corn and milk, then egg until mixed; stir into dry ingredients until batter is just blended.
Spoon batter into preheated molds.
Bake 15 minutes or until done.
Cool in molds on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from molds.

title: pork chop scallop
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Grease 10-inch skillet with fat. Brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from skillet.
Empty potatoes and seasoned sauce packet into skillet.
Stir in pimiento and amounts of milk and water called for on package.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; place pork chops on top.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Put cornflakes in a large bowl and pour syrup mixture over cornflakes.
Stir until coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa, salt, milk and egg yolks together.
Cook in microwave until thick, about 8 minutes, on High.
Add oleo and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Put in cooked pie shell.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add mushroom soup, salt, pepper, mushrooms, spinach and eggs.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: sad cake squares
directions: Combine coconut, baking mix, brown sugar and nuts.
Add eggs. Mix with spoon.
Do not overmix!
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan for 40 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tuna cheese wedges
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce.
Add all ingredients together and spread over 12 English muffins.

title: scallops, shrimp and snow peas
directions: Saute shrimp and scallops in small batches in a wok until done (shrimp first, then scallops; scallops take a few minutes to cook).
Set aside in dish, keeping warm.
Put a bit more oil in wok.
Quickly saute garlic, green onions and peppers, then add snow peas and continue sauteing.
Saute until peas are bright green and are cooked, yet crunchy.
Add scallops and shrimp.
Add broth, soy sauce and spices.
Thicken with a mixture of cornstarch and water (1/2 cup water and 1 tablespoon cornstarch).
Cook for about 7 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and cook until transparent; do not brown.
Wash and trim broccoli, peeling the stems.
Add sliced broccoli, potatoes and broth to onion in pan. Bring to boil and season.
Simmer, covered, until broccoli is tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add parsley last 3 minutes.
Drain broth from cooked vegetables and puree the broccoli mixture in blender.
Combine with broth and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, stir in the half and half.
This soup may be served hot or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, using 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Put in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 cup grated cheese on top of casserole. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry-lemon muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in blueberries which have been mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar, the peel of 1 lemon and the juice of that lemon.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine and let stand Bran Buds and boiling water.
Cream sugar, margarine, eggs, then add buttermilk, flour sifted with baking soda, salt and All-Bran cereal.
Add first mixture of bran buds and boiling water and combine with second mixture.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel, cut and boil potatoes until tender.
Cook remaining ingredients slowly in double boiler until cheese melts.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
For a spicier dish, use Mexican Velveeta.

title: best yet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased only).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherried cranberries
directions: Put all ingredients and 1 cup water in heavy 4-quart pan. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Do not uncover during cooking or cooling.
Store in jars in refrigerator.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and sweet peppers in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add few tablespoons of water, if necessary.
Add scallions, parsley, salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Add crawfish tails; cook 5 minutes or until done.
Serve over white rice.

title: italian sausage and bean soup
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces; brown in large heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon fat. Stir in onions; cook 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until soft, but not browned.
Stir in garlic and celery; cook until soft, 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in cabbage, tomatoes, beans, chicken broth, thyme, basil, oregano and bay leaf.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in almonds.

title: sausage-egg bake
directions: Spread bread cubes in buttered 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Layer sausage and cheese over bread.
Combine eggs and mustard with 1 generous cup of milk in a
bowl, beating well.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Blend 1/4 cup of milk with soup until smooth.
Pour over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings, about 350 calories each.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large ovenproof skillet, brown chops in oil.
Remove chops from skillet.
Pour off fat.
In skillet, combine ReaLemon and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add sugar, onion, soy sauce and bouillon.
Let bouillon dissolve.
Add pork chops and carrots.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.
Add pineapple chunks.
Cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with green pepper.
Serve with rice if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa and add enough milk to make it like a paste.
Then add the egg yolks and beat well.
Then add the balance of the milk and cook on top of the stove until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare and quarter potatoes.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in the bag, coating potatoes well with cheese mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 375 ° for about 1 hour, turning once during baking when golden brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease (12) muffin tin. Beat egg, then stir in milk and oil. Blend dry ingredients, then add the wet ingredients, stirring until moist. Add berries and fold in. Fill tins and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown beef; drain and put in cooker.
Brown bacon and onion; drain.
Add to cooker.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: yummy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup; shape into balls and place on a greased baking dish.
Pour the soup, thinned with water over the Yummy Balls and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: top of the stove baked beans
directions: Brown together ground beef with onion powder.
Drain off excess grease.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Stir and simmer until thick.

title: butter rum cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and beat until smooth. Pour into well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Mix last 4 ingredients together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Poke holes in cake while still in pan and hot.
Pour glaze over cake and let set for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: In bowl, stir together mushroom soup, milk, dry onion soup mix and undrained mushrooms.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the soup mixture and set aside.
Stir uncooked rice and thawed vegetables into remaining soup mixture.

title: apple candy pie
directions: Put apples in baking dish (greased) and sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add water.
Melt butter and add it to 1/2 cup brown sugar and flour.
Mix well and put on top of apple mixture, patting it down firmly.
Bake 3/4 hour to one hour in 350° oven.
Serve with cream.

title: quick lunch box cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate and nuts.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add chocolate and nuts and mix.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
(Skin, debone and tear into small pieces.)
Mix chicken pieces, cream of chicken soup (not diluted), onions and peppers.
