Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with corn oil. Layer chips, soup mixture and cheese until soup mixture is gone. Final layer of chips and sprinkle top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; cook for 5 more minutes.
Allow to cool for 10 minutes and serve.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly (do not sift). Add shortening, unbeaten egg and sour milk.
Beat only until smooth. Fill well oiled muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in hot oven at 425° about 25 minutes.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard, brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.

title: peanut buster dessert
directions: Mix together butter and pat 3/4 of the cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream that has been softened.
Put in freezer until firm.
Before serving, cover with fudge topping (not syrup); sprinkle with peanuts and cover with Cool Whip.
Use the 1/4 cup of Oreo cookies on top.

title: peach salad
directions: Bring pineapple, water and sugar to a boil; remove from heat. Add jellos.
Chill until partially set.
Whip slightly before adding other ingredients.

title: blueberry pie (low-fat)
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a good boil.
Heat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in a Dutch oven.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and vanilla and pour mixture over oleo.
Using a cup, pour berries over the mixture. Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: crescent cheese danish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay out 1 package of rolls in bottom of pan.
Pinch seams together.
Mix cream cheese, 1 egg and 1 yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon over rolls.
Take other package of rolls and spread on top.
(I lay rolls out on waxed paper first so I can push out to right size.)
Brush slightly whipped egg white on top.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Chill.
Great for breakfast or as dessert.

title: allison's peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put peach slices in square casserole dish.
In separate bowl, work together the sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and margarine until crumbly.
Add the lemon rind and mix.
Sprinkle over top of fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until the peaches are tender and the top is browned.
This takes about 20 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: turkey barbecue(40 mini sandwiches)
directions: Brown ground turkey in large skillet or saucepan; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except buns.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until thickened.
Serve in buns.

title: belleville gooey bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cake mix and 1 egg until crumbly.
Press into bottom of pan.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs, lemon juice and sugar (except for 1 tablespoon of the sugar) and pour onto cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with reserved sugar and cool. Cut into squares.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Cook veggies to your liking.
Saute onion in margarine. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in the milk.
Gradually heat to boiling;
stir constantly. Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients (broth, cheese, mustard).
Heat thoroughly.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In oven, melt shortening in baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Measure flour, salt, paprika and pepper into paper or plastic bag.
Shake 2 or 3 chicken pieces at a time in bag until thoroughly coated.
Place skin side down in shortening. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake until tender, 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream peanut
butter,
margarine
and vanilla together. Add powdered sugar and	mix
well.
Form
into balls and chill until firm.
Using a toothpick, quickly dip and swirl balls in Chocolate Dip, leaving a tan uncoated area around toothpick to resemble a buckeye.
Place on waxed paper and chill.

title: cassie's pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except pecans, for approximately 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: eggplant soup
directions: Steam onion and celery in hot oil and butter in tightly covered pot for about 10 minutes on low heat.
Add eggplant and potatoes and steam 15 minutes.
Stir in next 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Puree in blender.
Add cayenne and cream.
Serve hot or cold. Freezes well.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2-quart.
You may add green onion tops if you wish.

title: hoppin' john
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, celery and garlic in hot olive oil until onion is soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to a boil; reduce heat and cover tightly.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in proper sized buttered baking dish.
Dot generously with butter.
Bake, uncovered, slowly until bread browns a bit, at least 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: snickers pie or cake
directions: Cook cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake gets done, take out of oven and poke holes all in the cake.
Take your Smucker's caramel and condensed milk, already mixed together, and pour over cake.
Take the Snickers bars, sliced thin (to melt) and put on top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Very rich!

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend in large bowl the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Mix bowls together.
Stir in whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips. Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 14 minutes. Cool; cut into bars (about 2 x 1 1/2 inches).
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out flat in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour beaten eggs over dough.
Spread fried sausage over eggs.
Add hash browns (uncooked) over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and browned.
Serves 6.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Place whole
peeled
peaches in lightly salted water to soak and prevent darkening,
no
more
than 20 minutes.
Bring water and sugar to a
boil
in pot.
Add pickling spice.
Keep boiling. Drop peaches in hot liquid;
they will change color. Spoon peaches into hot
sterilized jars.
Cover with syrup and seal.
Try small pod of hot pepper in a few jars.

title: peas and rice
directions: Fry salt pork to get the fat.
Add onion, tomato, salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir all together and continue cooking.
Add peas and 3 cups water.
Let come to a boil and stir in rice.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and water absorbed.
Add another cup of water and cover to swell the rice.
Add more water, if needed. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: raspberry crisscross cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening as for pie.
Add eggs and milk.
Keep 1/4 of dough out.
Spread rest on 10 x 15-inch cake tin.
Press dough well up along side of pan.
Spread with jam. Sprinkle with nuts.
Pinch off pieces of reserved dough with palms of hands and make 1/2-inch strips.
Place on top for crisscross at 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan.
Cut with sharp knife in center of each strip so that each piece has dough around.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: In small bowl, combine reserved pineapple juice, pudding mix and Tang; set aside.
In large bowl, combine all the fruit.
Fold juice mixture into fruit.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese in bowl. Add pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt. Add pecans (reserving some to roll ball into). Form into a ball and chill. Roll in nuts just before serving.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Heat in double boiler until melted, then mash up pimiento pepper real good.
Remove from boiler and stir for a few minutes longer.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in microwave-safe mixing bowl. Merely place milk and margarine in bowl, but do not mix.
Cook in microwave on High power for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from microwave and stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts and stir until well blended and begins to thicken about 2 minutes or so.

title: top heavy coconut cake
directions: Make cake by box directions.
Bake as directed.
When has about 15 minutes left in oven, put sugar and pineapple in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Poke holes in cake and pour mixture over entire cake.
Place in refrigerator. Cool completely.
Make pudding and pour over cake.
Use 1/2 coconut and Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Put over cake.
Then top with remainder of coconut.
Then take your hand and push coconut into Cool Whip so it doesn't fall off cake.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients as you would for meat loaf.
Form into small balls; brown in frying pan. Drain grease and place meat balls in a baking dish. Cover with jar of spaghetti sauce. Cover with foil. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: bubble up pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Chop all ingredients, then add sauce mix. Cut biscuits in half, then in half again. Then mix with spaghetti sauce. Put in 13 x 9 pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 375° for 23 to 28 minutes.

title: perpetual pot of fruit with rum or brandy
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and rum or brandy (or some of both).
Pour into a large container with cover. Add fruit to the syrup, making sure that the fruit is submerged. Refrigerate, replenishing as needed.
Keeps beautifully.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion, soup, egg, salt, pepper and crumbs. Put in a baking dish.
Mix together soup, mustard, sugar, water and vinegar and pour over beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in uncooked pie shell.

title: carrot dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat all ingredients until smooth and even color.
Sprinkle paprika or cut chives on top.
Serve with carrots.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; slowly beat in sugar and salt. Add 1 egg at a time and beat briskly. Blend entire mixture. Pour into pastry lined pie pan for 8-inch pie. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until custard sets, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: viennese brownies
directions: In a bowl, combine softened cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg.
Add almond extract; set aside.
In small saucepan melt chocolate and butter together.
Cool.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add sugar and chocolate mixture.
Beat in sifted and combined flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour half the chocolate mixture into a well-greased and floured square baking pan (8-inches).
Gently spread the cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes, until cake tester inserted in center comes away clean.
Cool in pan before cutting into rectangles or squares.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients. Add eggs, pumpkin and oil. Blend in nuts. Grease and flour 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
You may use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir once or twice during baking.

title: raspberry mousse(makes 8 to 10 servings.)
directions: In small saucepan, combine 1 package undrained raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Chill thoroughly.
In blender, combine remaining 1 package drained raspberries, Eagle Brand and ReaLemon brand; blend until smooth. Place in large bowl; stir in food coloring if desired.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon half the mousse mixture into dessert dishes; top with equal portions of raspberry sauce, then remaining mousse mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: tomato salad in a bread bowl
directions: Cut a thin slice off top of bread.
Carefully cut out most of the inside of the bread, leaving a shell.
Tear insides into large, irregular pieces.
Toss lightly under broiler.
Set aside.

title: deep dish apple dish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 8-inch glass baking dish.
Place half of apples in dish; top with corn syrup.
Add remaining apples, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg. Combine 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, sugar, salt, butter, flour and oatmeal.
Mix well and press firmly over apples.
Bake 50 minutes. Top with ice cream and serve.

title: triple layer party pie
directions: In medium bowl combine butterscotch pudding mix, 2/3 cup nonfat dry milk powder and 1 1/4 cups water.
Mix well using a wire whisk. Pour into pie crust.
In medium bowl combine chocolate pudding mix, remaining 2/3 cup nonfat dry milk and remaining 1 1/4 cups water. Mix well using wire whisk.
Pour over butterscotch layer.
Cover and chill in refrigerator until set, about one hour.

title: green bean roll-ups
directions: Drain juice from green beans and reserve.
Cut bacon in half. In each slice of bacon, roll up 3 or 4 green beans.
Secure bacon with toothpicks.
Add part of green bean juice to the roll-ups after placing the roll-ups in a baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake until bacon browns.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter in bowl with electric mixer.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into egg batter.
Shape into balls; roll in additional granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately press a chocolate kiss into each cookie.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° until lightly browned or until done.

title: kraut soup
directions: Boil pork chops and potatoes until cooked.
Saute onion in pan and roll in flour.
Add 1 large can of tomatoes and string kraut.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar and shortening; add molasses.
Mix well.
Add beaten egg.
Stir together all remaining ingredients.
Mix into molasses mixture until thoroughly combined. Cover and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls, then place balls into granulated
sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in egg and pineapple juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Bring water to boiling point with salt according to directions on acini de pepe box.
Add oil and cook acini de pepe only until tender but firm.
Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Combine egg mixture with acini de pepe, mixing lightly.
Refrigerate overnight in an airtight container.
The next morning, add remaining ingredients. Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Refrigerate in airtight container until well chilled.
Salad may be refrigerated for a week, if desired.

title: coca-cola ham steak
directions: Cut each end of ham so ham steak won't curl.
Pour the Coke over the ham in skillet. Cook over medium heat.
Keep turning until Coke has vanished.
Ham will be done. Serve with a slice of pineapple on top.

title: key lime cake with frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9x13-inch pan.

title: children's edible play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
If it gets too sticky, put in a little flour.
Feeds six children.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured 3 loaf pans size 7 1/2 x 3 x 2-inch.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Very good served with fresh fruit.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Mix together.
Microwave on High until bubbling or bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine.
With a fork, blend in peanut butter.
Slowly, adding sugar, mix together with hands.
Roll into 2 or 3 long rolls.
Pinch off enough for small balls.
Place on wax paper or cookie sheet in freezer for 15 minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix the sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Use wooden spoon and stir in oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, add bananas.
Serves 6.

title: quesidillas(kay-sa-de-ya)
directions: Soften cream cheese; then add olives and enough salsa to make mixture pink.
Place 1 tortilla on plate (or server) and spread cheese mixture; repeat process ending with tortilla on top.
Cut into small slices like pie.
For garnish, fasten stuffed olive on each slice with toothpick.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler; cool.
Beat eggs and salt until light and foamy.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla and continue beating until well creamed.
With a few strokes (mix manually), combine chocolate into egg/sugar mixture.
Before mixture becomes uniformly colored, fold in flour.
Again, before mixing is uniformly colored, gently stir in pecans or walnuts. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars and mix well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 10 minutes at 350°, then 40 minutes at 300°.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and bring to a boil.
Blend to the mixture the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients, except round steak, in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Simmer gently for 5 minutes.
Pound steak (break tissues).
Cut into serving pieces.
Put in a large pan.
Pour barbecued sauce over meat.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Mix Miracle Whip with sugar; add vinegar (enough to make very tart).
Cut up eggs.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover and cool.

title: red-skinned mashed potatoes
directions: Add salt and soybean oil to 1 quart water.
Bring to a boil and add potatoes until fork-tender.
Remove potatoes and add butter, heavy cream, pepper and sour cream.
Mash.
Serves 4.

title: malaysian beef
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix together ginger, chili powder, garlic and lemon rind.
Dip meat into mixture and brown in butter.
Combine sugar, jam, lemon juice, salt and 1 1/2 cups water.
Add meat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine milk, margarine, sugar and salt in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High until margarine melts.
When lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in flour.
Let rise 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Dip in melted butter.
Place balls in baking pan. Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: elephant ears
directions: Stir flour, 2 tbsp. sugar, baking soda, and salt. Stir in milk and 3 tbsp. of melted butter. Mix until dough forms.
Sprinkle surface lightly with flour. Knead dough 10 times.
Roll dough, with rolling pin into a rectangle 9x5 inches.

Brush with remaining melted butter. Sprinkle mixture of 3 tbsp. sugar and cinnamon. Roll dough up tightly, beginning at narrow end. Pinch end of dough to seal. Cut into 4 equal pieces. Place cut side up on greased cookie sheet. Pat into circle. Sprinkle with more sugar. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 min. Remove from cookie sheet immediately. Let cool on wire rack.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in 1 gallon boiling water and pour over cukes. Let stand 5 to 7 days.
Rinse.
Dissolve 2 tablespoons alum in 1 gallon boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours.
Rinse and split cukes (no matter how small); repeat 2 tablespoons alum in 1 gallon boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Rinse thoroughly.
Prepare equal parts sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Pour over cukes. Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off and add equal parts of sugar to vinegar solution.
Bring to a boil and pour over cukes that have been packed in jars.
Seal.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Combine skim milk, strawberries, orange juice and sugar substitute in container of an electric blender or food processor. Process until strawberries are pureed and mixture is frothy. Transfer mixture to a small pitcher.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into individual glasses and serve immediately.
Diabetic Exchange: 1 skim milk.
Each serving amount:
1 cup.
Calories:

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into casserole.

title: zesty chicken pot pie
directions: Cook cream cheese and broth in large saucepan on low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently with wire whisk. Stir in chicken, vegetables and salad dressing mixes. Spoon into 9-inch pie plate. Cover with 1 pie crust; seal and flute edge. Cut several slits to permit steam to escape. Cut remaining pie crust into decorative shapes; arrange on crust. Place pie plate on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: salted pumpkin seeds
directions: Boil dry seeds for 5 minutes.
Spray baking sheet with pam. spread seeds on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350 degrees until dry. Serve warm or cool.

title: rock road cake icing
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a small pan. Add cocoa, conf. sugar and milk. Stir and heat until everything is blended. Pour over cake (leave in pan) and spread.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Heat cola and oleo to boiling point.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and stir with spoon until they are coated.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs (cocktail)
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg and next 3 ingredients.
Make 1/2 to 1-inch size meatballs.
Put shortening/oil in a skillet and cook until golden brown.
Drain grease.
In crock-pot preheat chili and jelly.
After heated place meatballs in crock-pot.
Let simmer approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: "company" bread
directions: Trim
crust
off top and sides of loaf of French bread. Cut X's across top.
Place Swiss cheese, cut in small pieces, in
X's. In
pan
melt butter, mustard, onion, poppy seed and lemon juice until all is dissolved.
Spoon over bread and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into two 8-inch pie shells or 1 large pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: box honey graham crackers
directions: Break graham crackers into sections and line bottom of pan. Bring butter to boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers and add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: First, brown hamburger.
Drain the meat.
Take 13 x 9-inch glass pan and butter both sides and bottom.
Spread biscuits on both bottom and sides.
Put meat on top of biscuits, then put vegetables on top of meat.
Put a little bit of water on top. Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Pull out and put potatoes and cheese on top.
Put back in oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Place rice on bottom of casserole dish. Place uncooked chicken on top of rice. Pour onion soup mix over chicken. Mix milk, soup and 1 soup can of water together. Pour over top of all. Bake at 325° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients gradually into liquid mixture. Pour into four (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Remove while warm and wrap in foil.

title: peachy cobbler
directions: Arrange drained peaches in a square baking pan.
Pour lemon juice and spread brown sugar over peaches.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a bowl; set aside.
Bring the oleo, cocoa and water to a boil and add to the flour mixture.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and add to the other mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, in a well-greased cookie sheet pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix one cornbread mix according to directions on box and add 1/2 can corn.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer hamburger, picante sauce, cheese and the other cornbread mix, mixed according to directions, adding the other half of the corn. Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Cut bacon into 1/4-inch strips and cook slowly until crisp.
When bacon is half done, add onion and cook until soft.
Drain off fat.
Combine bacon and onion with eggs, celery and olives.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix.
Stuff tomatoes and serve on lettuce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corns with butter and sour cream.
Add eggs and stir in muffin mix.
Bake in a 9-inch pie pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, 3/4 cup water and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour. Meanwhile, combine sugar, margarine and 1/4 cup water in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, and remove from heat.
When cake is done, immediately pour sauce slowly over cake, allowing time for it to be absorbed.
Leave cake in pan for 20 minutes before removing.

title: cheese and vegetable casserole
directions: Heat milk; pour over bread crumbs.
Add pimento, parsley, onion, grated cheese and seasonings, then add eggs.
Put the vegetables in a greased or oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole; pour milk and cheese mixture over them.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour, or until firm.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain excess fat and set aside.
Combine cornbread mixes together according to directions on box. Additionally, add 1/3 cup milk and can of corn to the cornbread mixes.

Using a nonstick spray, prepare a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Pour a small amount of cornbread batter in pan to form a layer. Sprinkle meat mixture on top and then sprinkle grated cheese on top of the meat.
Pour remaining cornbread mix on top of all and bake according to box directions.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and nutmeg; add egg yolks.
Mix. Add sour cream, raisins, lemon juice and nuts.
Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue on top and brown.

title: caf viennese
directions: Process in blender on liquefies until well blended. Store in airtight container.

title: savory fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
In large bag, combine flour and seasonings.
In shallow bowl, beat eggs and water.
Place chicken a few pieces at a time in bag and shake to coat.
Dip in eggs and shake in bag again.
Fry chicken until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange drink
directions: Blend all ingredients until creamy looking.

title: fruited coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, marshmallows, pineapple, apple, celery and enough salad dressing to moisten. Toss lightly and chill.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until lightly browned.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put vegetables and salt into ice water; let stand for 3 hours. Drain.
Bring to
boil vinegar, sugar and spices.	Add squash, onions and peppers; boil
for
minutes and put into jars and seal.

title: limas in casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce, and tomato paste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Spoon mixture into greased baking dish.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Place biscuits near outer edge of hot meat mixture, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese in center and around edge. Gently brush biscuits with margarine and sprinkle with oregano. Bake for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: chocolate-almond frosting
directions: Mix butter with coffee, salt and chocolate.
Add rest of ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Beat until creamy and frost tops and sides of cakes.

title: rice and broccoli dish
directions: Saute chopped onion in melted margarine until tender.
Add the mushroom soup.
Cut up 1/3 of a small box of Velveeta or American cheese.
Add to onion and soup mixture.
Melt cheese with mixture. Add 2 cups cooked rice and 10 ounces of frozen broccoli (thawed and drained).
Pour in buttered casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients like pie dough. Put half in 8 inch square pan. Mix remaining ingredients. Spread on crumbs. Put remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Drop on greased sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: "miss" jean's squash casserole
directions: Combine melted butter with dressing mix.
Sprinkle small amount in casserole dish.
Save
enough
to cover top of casserole and combine the rest of crumbs with the other ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle the reserved crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp (uncooked) and devein.
Make roux (dark) of flour and oil.
Add shrimp to this for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef cubes in oil.
Add water, salt and pepper for seasonings.
Simmer slowly until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and cook 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 11 g, fat 12 g, calories 180. One serving = 1 1/2 meat medium fat exchange, 1 vegetable exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar, beat egg and add to mixture.
Tear bread slices and add with pineapple to first mixture.
Mix together.
Place in 1 1/2 to 2-quart greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: rachel's fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts.
Place all nuts, drained cherries and dates in a large bowl.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together. Coat the fruit and nuts with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla to eggs and pour over coated fruit and nuts; mix well.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together.
Beat egg whites and water until it's meringue consistency.
Add sugar mixture 1 tablespoon at a time.
Beat to a stiff peak.
Fold in pecan halves.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans and press into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecan mixture.
Melt butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well and drop by tablespoons on top of cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or when cracks form in center of cake.
Do not overcook.
No icing needed.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Sift flour.
Beat eggs in 2 cup measuring cup with wire whisk. Whisk
in	milk and oil. Stir just until moistened. Do not beat. Fill
greased
and floured muffin pan 2/3 full. For Surprise Muffins, fill 1/2 full, then drop 1 teaspoon of jelly or preserves in center. Add more batter to make 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: baked applesauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first four ingredients in a buttered casserole dish.
Put butter on top of applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: autumn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13x9 inch pan. Top with topping mix.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello in hot water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add cool water.
Set in refrigerator to cool until thick
(soft).
Add ground fruits, nuts and liquids.
Mix then pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.

title: sponge cake roll
directions: Let egg whites stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Sift flour and salt and set aside.
Coat a 15x10x1 baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Line with wax paper and coat the paper with spray.
In a mixing bowl, beat yolks until slightly thickened. Gradually add sugar and beating until thick and lemony colored. Add orange peel, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add sifted flour mixture and mix well.
Batter will be thick.
In another bowl beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake at 350 for 12-15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes. Turn onto a kitchen towel.
Sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. powdered sugar. Gently pull wax paper off and roll cake up jelly roll style, starting with short side.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Unroll cake- spread marmalade evenly over cake within 1/2 inch of edges. Roll up again, seam side down.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar. Wrap and place in refrigerator one hour.
Servings 8 - 5 Points.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in the Parkay and add the nuts. Mix in egg and soda. Press half of mixture in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 1-gallon freezer.
Finish filling with whole milk.
Stir and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown and firm.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Simmer tomatoes in large saucepan for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup butter, soda, 1 teaspoon salt and sugar.
Let cool during preparation of next step.
Melt the remaining 1/4 cup butter in large kettle.
Add flour and 2 teaspoons salt.
Add milk; heat and stir to boiling point.
Combine the two mixtures and heat slowly.
Add salt, if needed, and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into prepared crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Blend half and half and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken spread
directions: Cook chicken in unsalted water to cover until tender.
Remove from broth, reserving 2 tablespoons broth.
Cool.
Bone chicken; chop fine.
Combine cheese and mayonnaise, beating until smooth. Add onion, pickle juice, celery, curry powder, salt, pepper, pimiento, hot sauce and garlic powder; mix well.
Stir in chicken and broth.
Serve on crackers or lettuce leaves.
Each tablespoon contains about 22 calories.

title: chicken carrie
directions: Use a skillet or wok.
Saute onion, green pepper, salt and pepper in chicken fat.
Place potatoes on top of ingredients in skillet or wok, then chicken breasts on top of potatoes.
Pour in broth.
Cover and simmer gently, about 30 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Bring water, gelatine, sugar and pineapple to boil.
Cook for five minutes.
Remove from stove and while hot add cream cheese and cream.
Stir until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into mold or decorative bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: dressing for fresh fruits
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients until smooth.
Chill about 2 hours.
Serve over fresh fruit salads.
Yield: 1 1/4 cups.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chocolate chips.
Keep over heat until melted.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Mix well. Spread on bottom of deep 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Combine canned or cooked pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Blend in beaten egg and evaporated milk.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until done.
Cool.
May be topped with Cool Whip or cream.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Refrigerate prepared pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar, syrup, flour, salt and vanilla. Combine well.
Stir in butter and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes or until filling is set in center.
May cover crimped pie crust edges with foil so edges don't overcook.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cube steak and brown in skillet with garlic and pepper and a little oil.
Add soy sauce and water.
Cover and cook 20 minutes. Add sliced bell peppers and onions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch and cold water to thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: red hot salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in hot water and add Jell-O.	Blend thoroughly and cool.
Add applesauce.
Pour in loaf pan and jell.

title: apple bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add brown sugar and rolled oats.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Spread half the mixture in a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
